title: bacon and cheese quiche
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Spoon into pie crust. Sprinkle onion with cheese.
Combine milk and eggs.
Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Pour into crust.
Crumble 2 pieces of bacon and sprinkle over pie.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Garnish with remaining bacon pieces.

title: instant tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a tightly sealed container.
To serve:
Put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of tea mixture in a cup of boiling water and enjoy a cup of cheer.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in crock-pot which has been lightly greased.
Cut thin slices of cheese and lay on top. Cook for 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter.
When butter is golden brown, add brown sugar and heat.
Stir in water, cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Cool. Pour into cooled baked pie shell.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in lightly greased (1 quart size) baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serves about 4 to 5.

title: old-time buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Add flour and eggs, beating well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmegs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Place on wire rack to cool completely before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine; press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Beat eggs, other 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar together in mixer for 15 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Spread egg mixture over crumb layer.
Slice bananas over this; spread the drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top; sprinkle with cherries and nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl; cut in 3/4 cup butter thoroughly. Blend until mixture resembles very fine crumbs. Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. (Use a piece of plastic wrap to press crumb mixture firmly in pan.) Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cream of chicken soup and set aside.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
On top of this, spread chicken and add soup mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turkey may also be used instead of chicken.

title: betsy's dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: tiger butter
directions: Line
10 1/2 x 15 1/2 inch jelly roll pan with wax paper. Microwave white chocolate 1 to 2 minutes and stir until smooth. Add peanut butter and stir until smooth again.
Spread in prepared pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Pour over first mixture and swirl with a knife.
Refrigerate.
When firm, break into pieces.

title: jiffy scalloped corn
directions: Soften butter; combine all ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (helps if sprayed with Pam).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Place Nilla wafers in bottom of cake pan.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding together.
Pour half of Cool Whip and pudding mixture over wafers.
Layer wafers and remainder of pudding mixture.
Microwave frosting to soften.
Pour frosting over last layer of wafers. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers (uncrushed).
Cover with pudding mixture.
Repeat layers as many as desired, ending with crackers.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta and clams
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add minced clams and clam juice in can.
Add parsley, oregano, basil, wine and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Make 2 servings of linguine or spaghetti.
Cook as directed on the package.
Do not overcook.
Drain and serve with clam sauce.
Sprinkle Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Gently squeeze the spinach, discarding excess water. Place in a nonaluminum saucepan and cook over a low heat, stirring constantly for about 5 minutes until it's tender, but still bright green. Add cream, salt and nutmeg and simmer for 5 minutes until the cream has bubbled and reduced slightly.

title: beans beans beans
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 to 3 hours, depending on consistency.

title: louisiana corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and salt.
Mix with noodles.

title: golden bricks
directions: In heavy boiler, add sugar, milk and margarine.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the Kisses and marshmallow cream.
Beat until smooth, then add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
This is a great recipe to share with friends at Christmas.
It makes a big batch and keeps well.

title: szechuan chicken
directions: Split chicken breast in half; skin and debone.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Put cornstarch in paper bag or plastic baggie. Add chicken pieces and toss lightly to coat.
Heat oil in electric frying pan.
Add chicken and garlic.
Stir-fry at 375° until chicken is lightly brown.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and water to skillet.
Cover and cook 3 minutes at 250° or until chicken is cooked through.
Uncover skillet; add green onions and cayenne pepper.
Heat 2 minutes longer and enjoy.

title: baked rice custard
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Place milk in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until almost boiling.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in sugar mixture.
Beat eggs and egg white until frothy.
Gradually stir 1/4 of hot mixture into eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Place baking dish in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add water to pan to depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir custard gently and bake 10 minutes.
Stir custard and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge of dish comes out clean.
Remove baking dish from water; cool.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Yields 9 servings (153 calories, 16% from fat per 1/2-cup serving).

title: barley casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Do not overcook.
Place barley in large casserole.
Add the above cooked ingredients; saute about 2 minutes.
Pour in bouillon; stir.
Cover casserole; place in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until liquid is absorbed and barley is al dente).
Prepare for exclamations of approval when served!

title: chocolate pound cake(bill wagner's)
directions: Cream the shortening and oleo together.
Add sugar and eggs. Mix together and sift the flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Put the dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and almond extract. Bake in a 350° oven using the cake test in 1 hour and 10 minutes. Use a 10-inch tube pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in oblong Pyrex dish.
Pour melted butter over stuffing mix; stir until well saturated.
Press half of stuffing mix in bottom of the Pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour in Pyrex.
Add the other half of stuffing mix on top of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Lightly grease a casserole dish or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Prepare corn bread as directed.
Brown meat, onions and bell peppers.
Add chili seasoning and tomatoes.
Pour 1/2 of the corn bread batter in pan, add meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Add remaining corn bread batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces. Saute in large pot. Add beans and all other ingredients. Mix well. Pour into casserole dish. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, until thickened. Serves 10.

title: rhubarb puffs
directions: Bring sugar, water and food coloring to a boil.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Place rhubarb in a 12 x 15-inch pan (pan should be about half full).
Pour syrup over rhubarb.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onion into 1/2-inch slices.
Skin, salt and pepper. Marinate in buttermilk, about 1 hour.
Pour 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour into a small paper bag.
Drop onion slices into bag and shake until well coated.
Drop into hot vegetable oil and fry until golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Make sauce first.
Brown ground beef in oil with onion, salt, garlic salt, basil, tomato paste, water, sugar, cinnamon, salt, pepper and oregano.
If possible, add 2 small Italian sausages. Remove casings and put meat with ground beef.
Simmer at least 2 hours or until sauce is thick.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split and clean seeds from chilies.
Cut cheese in small squares and roll in chilies.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in yolks and 6 tablespoons flour. Dip rellenos in flour and then in batter.
Brown in hot oil (remove toothpicks).
Heat salsa for topping.

title: deviled eggs and bacon
directions: Slice hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Mash yolks with fork and combine with dry ingredients first, then add wet ingredients second.
Blend well and add additional mayonnaise, if mixture not creamy enough texture.
Fill egg whites with mixture and top with chives.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix thawed juices well.
Chill.
Chill soda, then combine at serving time.
Mixture is yellow colored.
Decorate as you wish. Any leftover may be frozen and used as a floating mold the next time you serve this.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Gradually add in flour and baking soda.
Drop tablespoon size dollop on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces. Add chopped egg whites and chopped onions, including onion tops.
In a small bowl, mash egg yolks.
Add vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over lettuce and mix until each piece is coated.
Heat bacon drippings and pour over lettuce. Crumble bacon over all and mix well.
Serve at once. Serves 4.

title: fudge cake(yields 48 portions)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and mix on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Mix cocoa and hot water.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and cocoa to creamed mixture on low speed.
Scrape sides of bowl.
Continue mixing until smooth and all ingredients are mixed.

title: never fail gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and molasses. Add dry ingredients alternately with hot water, beating until smooth. Bake in a greased 6 x 10-inch pan. Serve hot or cool.

title: gracie's corn meal mush
directions: Moisten corn meal with the cold milk, then turn immediately into boiling salted water.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens. Turn heat down to simmer and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn cooked mush into a square cake pan.
When cold, slice into 1/2 inch slices and fry in a hot iron skillet.
Spray skillet with Pam first, then add Crisco oil.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together hamburger and sausage; season to taste with onions.
Beforehand, cook rice until fluffy.
Add cooked rice to meat mixture.
Mix tomatoes.
Mix it all together well.
Take lose leaves of cabbage.
Wrap meat mixture in leaves of cabbage, holding together with toothpicks.
Cover with ketchup.
Allow enough liquid in pressure cooker to cover ingredients.
Cook 13 pounds pressure for 8 minutes or if cooked on stove top in open kettle, it will take 3 hours, or 10 pounds pressure for 30 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together, put in jar and refrigerate.

title: no cook play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt, oil and alum.
Add a small amount of water at a time until the mixture is the consistency of bread dough.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Grease 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sky high lemon chiffon pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix unflavored gelatine with 1/2 cup sugar; blend in egg yolks beaten with water and lemon juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes; add lemon peel.
Pour into large bowl and chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Clean and core tomatoes and cut in quarters.
Bring to boil and stir often, until they are well cooked.
(Don't add water.) Put tomatoes through a sieve and store juice in clean jars for a day in refrigerator, until water comes to top of jar.
Take off water and use only the bottom part.
Now, cook your onions, peppers and garlic in oil until tender.
Cool a little, then put in blender until well blended.
Add this and other ingredients to your tomato juice and cook in large pot until thick.
Some only cook it 30 minutes, but I did mine a couple of hours.
Use your own judgement.
Scald your jars and lids.
Put the sauce in them and you are done.

title: rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, put in 3 cups flour, salt, dry yeast and powdered milk.
Mix together.
Heat water, sugar and shortening to a little more than lukewarm.
Add to dry mixture, plus 2 eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add 3 more cups flour and work by hand or dough breaker until quite elastic.
Cover with waxed paper and put a dark towel over it.
Yeast grows better in a dark area.
Set it in a nice warm area to rise until double in size.

title: italian lamb chop and potato bake
directions: Coat small roasting pan with Crisco or Pam.
Trim chops; rub with 1 clove of garlic.
Arrange chops in pan.
Mix bread crumbs, parsley, chopped garlic, salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix cut potatoes with a bit of oil, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of chops.
Drizzle oil over crumbs.
Spread potatoes on top of chops and bread crumbs.
Add water into each corner.
Bake at 375°; cover with foil the first 1/2 hour.
Remove foil; continue baking until potatoes brown and chops are fork-tender.
Potatoes should also be soft.
Total cooking time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue glaze
directions: Put all ingredients into container of electric blender; blend for a few seconds (until smooth).
Pour into small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Crumble into pieces.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Then layer all ingredients ending with Cool Whip, nuts and maraschino cherries.
(Put this in a punch bowl or a large glass bowl.)

title: nancy's favorite veggies
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Cook veggies according to package; drain.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix in sour cream, flour, salt, pepper and butter.
Place slices of cheese over all. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves approximately six.

title: grandma's crabmeat dip
directions: Thoroughly blend with fork the crabmeat, cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry onion flakes.
Mix directly in baking dish. Even out mixture with fork.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: super quick fish sandwiches(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spread crumbs on waxed paper.
Beat egg white.
Dip fish in egg and press on crumbs to coat.
Place on rack in pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until fish is opaque and crumbs are browned.
Serve on rolls with tartar sauce.

title: squash and tomato parmesan
directions: Pare squash and cut in thirds.
Simmer in covered skillet in 1 inch of stock until tender (about 8 minutes).
Remove squash to broiler pan.
Sprinkle with half the salt, pepper, basil and garlic.
Slice tomatoes thinly and place over squash.
Sprinkle with remaining spices and cheese.
Broil 3 inches from heat until cheese is brown (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 350° about an hour or until lightly brown.

title: orange sherbet jell-o
directions: Combine the jell-o and boiling water stirring well until jell-o is dissolved.
Add the orange sherbet and mix well.
Add the mandarin orange slices and chopped nuts; chill.
Prepare the topping by mixing the mashed banana with 1/2 of the Cool Whip; add the pineapple and mayonnaise.
Fold into the rest of the Cool Whip and spread over the jell-o.
Chill well before serving.

title: eggplant and tomato parmesan(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat 8-inch square glass baking dish with vegetable oil.
Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Layer in prepared dish; top with tomatoes.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients except cheeses.
Spread over vegetables; sprinkle evenly with Mozzarella cheese and then Parmesan cheese. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Exchanges:
2 vegetables, 1/2 bread and 1 lean meat.

title: voni's fabulous chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish. Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Mix mushrooms, sugar and sherry together and pour mixture over chicken. Pour 1/3 bag of stuffing on top.
Drizzle topping with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of crumbs on bottom, then add rest on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and stir ground chuck until light brown.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook several minutes. Stir in stewed tomatoes, soup, water, cabbage, salt, pepper, chili powder and brown sugar.
Simmer until done.
You might want to add small V-8 or tomato juice.

title: cooter's cowboy dip
directions: Mix with an electric mixer.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: In a large skillet brown lean sausage.
Drain.
Remove from pan.
Brown hash browns according to directions on package. Remove from pan.
Beat eggs slightly and pour into pan.
Cook slightly, then add cooked sausage and hash browns.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When eggs are firm, add chunked Velveeta cheese. Turn on very low heat and put lid on skillet.
Prepare tortilla shells.
Add filling, roll up and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, milk and salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables, macaroni and egg.

title: string pie
directions: Hollow out oblong rolls; brush with melted butter.
Heat in moderate hot oven (400°) until hot and crusty.
Fill with barbecued hamburger, tuna, deviled ham, egg or chicken (all except hamburger made with mayonnaise).
Garnish each with a sprig of parsley.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and oregano.
Cook 20 minutes. Split rolls.
Measure evenly on bottom half of rolls and top with 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Close sandwich and wrap it in aluminum foil.
Heat in oven 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: potato casserole(also known as fiesta or texas potatoes)
directions: Defrost
potatoes.
Combine
in bowl chicken soup, sour cream, grated cheese and onions.
Mix together and place in a 9
x 13-inch
baking
dish
with melted oleo.
Top with bread crumbs. Cover
and
bake
to
40 minutes at 350°.
Can be baked ahead and reheated; also freezes well.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables.
Add enough water to cover barely and simmer covered over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Meantime, melt butter; add flour and blend.
Cook a minute or two, then add cream.
Cook and stir until smooth and thick.
Add clams, veggies and liquid. Season with salt, pepper and sugar and heat thoroughly.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream together until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; sprinkle with chopped pecans or walnuts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pork loin kabobs
directions: Cut
tenderloins in
2-inch
cubes.
Quarter
tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Place on skewers alternately.
Brush with oil. Sprinkle pinch of
rosemary
over
skewers	and top with minced garlic.
Place in broiler for approximately 15 minutes, turning frequently until done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mash and drain again.
Add everything else.
Mix and drop by spoonful in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: beef and noodles and sour cream
directions: Cook onion in margarine until soft, add ground beef and cook. Place noodles in layer on top of cooked meat.
Mix tomato juice, salt, celery salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Pour over noodles and beef.
Do not stir.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix thoroughly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Pour the melted butter or oleo over the bread seasoning.
Pour bread seasoning over vegetable, soup and mayonnaise in baking dish. Bake until brown on top (approximately 1/2 hour) in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie(yield: 2)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and salt.
Add syrup slowly.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour ingredients into 2 (9-inch) pie shells with pecans in bottom.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until 2-inch shaky middle.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease medium casserole dish; set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix in flour.
Gradually stir in broth; mix thoroughly.
Gradually add milk to saucepan.
Cook, stirring continually until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.
Bring 2 quarts water to boil.
Add noodles; cook 6 minutes, drain noodles.
Spread noodles in prepared dish.
Place chicken and broccoli over noodles.
Pour sauce over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, stir butter, mushroom soup and milk until smooth. Heat and stir, adding cooked chicken. Add peas and pepper. To spice it up, saut the onion, green pepper and pimento and add the basic recipe. Serve over toast or warm biscuits.

title: peanut divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 3-quart microwave bowl.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Uncover. Stir well.
Microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes or until it reaches hard ball stage.

title: chocolate whipped cream frosting
directions: Place whipping cream, sugar and cocoa in bowl in refrigerator (with beaters) for at least 1 hour.
Whip 1/2 hour before serving. Add vanilla last.
Serve on angel food, sponge or chiffon cake. Yields 3 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Scald milk.
Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar.
Slowly add sugar and cornstarch mixture to scalded milk, then the egg yolk mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Take off heat; add butter and vanilla.
Let cool. Beat egg whites with 8 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Pour egg yolk mixture into cooled pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: peach custard
directions: Add stiff egg whites last.
Fill unbaked pie shell 3/4 full of sliced ripe peaches.
Pour egg and flour mix over top of peaches until shell is full.
Pour small amount of melted butter on top. Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake on bottom rack.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: In medium glass bowl, crumble ground beef.
Stir in onions. Heat at High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until beef loses pink color.
Stir once; drain.
Stir in 1 can tomato sauce, water, 1 tablespoon cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat, covered with plastic wrap, at High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir in rice; let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds and rinse.
Spoon beef and rice filling into each half; place in oblong baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat at High 10 to 12 minutes, or until peppers are tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and warm slowly until margarine melts.
Stirring, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes more. Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
(Microwave is easier.)
Mix with onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in greased casserole. Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Put on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Pour off excess fat, leaving the brown drippings in the broiler pan.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water to pan; heat and stir. Season to taste.
Unthickened gravy is best for steaks.

title: jan hagels(cookies)
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy in a large bowl with electric mixer.
Add egg yolk and almond extract, blending thoroughly.
Stir in flour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt the first 5 ingredients.
Quarter biscuits and shake in Baggies with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Make first layer with 2 cans of biscuits, then pour 1/2 of syrup mixture over top. Arrange other 2 cans, pouring rest of syrup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use Bundt or tube pan.

title: bananas in sour cream
directions: Combine
sour
cream and sugar.
Slice bananas and stir gently into sour cream mixture.
Spoon into champagne glasses. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill.

title: k-nepp
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick. Cover well and cook about 15 minutes. Add salt.
Beat eggs in a bowl. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a stiff dough. Drop flour by teaspoon into potatoes. Cover and cook.
Pour into colander and drain.
Put into dish and cover with sauce.

title: grape pie
directions: Remove skins while cleaning grapes; reserve them until later. Put pulp in saucepan with no water!
Bring to a rolling boil.
Run through strainer to remove seeds while hot.

title: salted pecans(microwave)
directions: Pour nuts into colander and wet thoroughly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour into small casserole dish or glass pie plate. Microwave at High for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring at 2 minute intervals.
Cool nuts and serve.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Combine salad dressing, sugar and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with water, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into 2 wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool. Fill and frost with Creamy Cocoa Frosting.

title: 3 minute microwave fudge
directions: In a microwavable bowl, mix together the powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and milk; microwave on High for 2 minutes. Remove from microwave; stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows; microwave on High for 1 minute.
Remove from microwave.
Add vanilla; stir until smooth.
If desired, add walnuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch brownie pan.
Allow fudge mixture to set, then cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown bell pepper and onion in 1 stick margarine.
In casserole dish, combine rice, corn, soup, bell pepper and onion with butter, 1/2 cup cheese, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Mix together well and top with remaining cheese, then crumble crackers over top of cheese.
Melt margarine and pour over top of crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: milk chocolate fudge(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add both kinds of morsels and stir until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/4 pounds.

title: lucky if there's any left
directions: Mix and press flour, margarine and pecans into buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Then mix cream cheese and 1/2 tub Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Then mix instant pudding, confectioners sugar and milk.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread the other 1/2 of the 16-ounce tub of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with the pecans.
Chill.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie base by mixing together the water, brownie mix, oil and egg.
Pour onto greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer rinsed noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.

title: miss mary's "like fresh" corn
directions: Mix corn, cream, milk, sugar and salt.
Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly.
Melt butter and add flour to it.
Add to corn and cook until thick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients into a bowl until well mixed.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and rice
directions: Cook beef until done.
Cook onion and pepper with beef.
Put rice in pot.
Cook on low heat until done.
Salt and pepper to your taste.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3 qt. sauce pan bring water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onions and boil 10 - 12 minutes.
Add seasonings and shredded cheese, stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream, and butter. Stir and heat to boiling. Slowly add cold water to flour stirring constantly until texture is smooth.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir until soup is the consistency of heavy cream.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: tuna-macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and set aside.
Combine the next 7 ingredients together in a saucepan and cook over low heat until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, tuna and macaroni.
In an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 the macaroni mixture, 1/2 the Mozzarella and 1/2 the tomato slices.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. The tomato/cheese topping is very pretty.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Add onion, chilies, olives and taco seasoning to hot browned hamburger in frying pan.
Stir in beaten eggs and scramble all together until eggs are done.
Fill each tortilla with meat and egg mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and salsa, if desired.
Roll up burrito style and serve.

title: creole shrimp bake
directions: Fry the bacon until cooked, but not crisp.
Drain excess fat and add butter.
When butter is melted, add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: fried crawfish
directions: Season crawfish.
Dip in milk, then in seasoned flour.
Fry in deep cooking oil.
Brown well and drain on paper towel.
Serve with sliced tomatoes and hot sauce.

title: peanut butter icebox pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press into pie pan to form crust.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: herbed turkey loaf(low-fat loaf)
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, melt margarine on low. Saute onion until golden.
Set aside.
In a saucer soak bread in milk; break bread apart.
In a large bowl, combine onions, bread and remaining ingredients.
Mix with hands until thoroughly combined.
Shape into a loaf and place onto a lightly greased pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger, onion, garlic and oregano.
Drain off extra fat.
Add soup, water, vinegar and cottage cheese.
Stir all together.
In 9 x 13 inch pan put a little sauce, then you put 3 noodles then cheese.
Layer it 3 times in order.
Bake 30 minutes, let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cherry fruit squares
directions: Cream butter, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in flour.
Add nuts last.
Spread 3/4 of batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with cherry pie filling.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on top and spread it around with a spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired. Other fruit toppings can be used (apple, blueberry).

title: chicken or turkey enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Save chicken broth.
In large saucepan, saute onion, green pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chopped chicken and green chilies and set mixture aside.
In large saucepan, combine 3 tablespoons butter, flour, coriander, salt and chicken broth.
Stir until thickened.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Combine 1/2 cup of sauce mixture into the chicken mixture.
Roll each tortilla with chicken mixture and 1 tablespoon of sauce and place in large baking dish.
When rolling of tortillas is complete, sprinkle remaining cheese and then remaining sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients in your crock-pot.
Do not stir. Add together the next 6 ingredients, mix and pour over top of layers in crock-pot.
Cook at least 6 to 8 hours on low.
Stir before serving.

title: dennis' delicious meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drizzle a little Heinz 57 on top and bake at 350 for about 1 hour or until done.
Drain grease before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of Pyrex dish (8 x 8 x 3-inch).
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Top with Pepperidge Farm or Stove Top dressing that has been tossed with a little butter or margarine.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: turkey salad
directions: Serve with toasted wheat crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in oblong pan.
Layer pineapple over pie filling, sprinkle cake mix over top then layer coconut and pecans. Add butter and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in large pan.
Cook over low heat until a slight boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (use wax paper to press evenly and smoothly).
Melt bits in double boiler; stir until blended.
Spread over Rice Krispies mixture. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Remove; wait about 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Cut into bars.

title: angie's rolls
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into a large bowl. Add mayonnaise, and milk. Mix all ingredients together until well mixed. Place mixture into greased muffin pans and bake at 375 degrees until rolls are golden brown. Mixture can be halved.

title: mexican shuffles
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain and mix in the soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer as follows:
line bottom of oblong cake pan with 6 tortillas, then one can of beans (drained), 1/2 of the meat mixture and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Repeat layers as above. Cook, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lottie moon candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Add butter, coconut and peanuts.
Mix and spread on buttered plate. Cut while warm.

title: egg and shrimp casserole
directions: Butter	casserole.
Cover
bottom
of dish with deviled eggs. Mix
sharp cheese (and crabmeat and sherry, if desired) with white sauce.
Pour
some
sauce over eggs.
Add layer of shrimp,
then remaining
sauce.
Cover
with
buttered
bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
(I prefer adding cheese and crab to white sauce and eliminate sherry.)

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Drain apples and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Combine margarine, sugar, cheese and flour in double boiler and cook until creamy.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
One and one half times this recipe makes a 9 x 13-inch dish for 8 to 12 people.

title: parker county cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish. Combine dry ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup sugar. Stir into melted butter into baking dish. Add milk and stir again.

title: fast corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cream-style corn, evaporated milk, undrained whole kernel corn with sweet peppers, dried minced onion and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add margarine.
Serves 4 (1 cup each).

title: ellen's crisp cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt together.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate overnight.

title: basic fluffy rice
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Combine with rice, salt and butter in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not lift lid during baking.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Shape into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar and spice 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until thick.

title: country pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Mix really well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes in 425° oven. Turn oven down to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes more.
Makes 1 pie.

title: thai fettucini
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended.
Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture; toss remaining with cooked fettucini.

title: snack crackers
directions: Combine oil, dill weed, garlic powder and Ranch salad dressing. Pour over oyster crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.
I bake them for 2 hours at 200°.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put 2 tablespoons of Mazola into the 1/3 cup buttermilk; stir well.
Pour into sifted ingredients.
Stir with a spoon.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 3 minutes; add sugar and beat for 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice, mixing well.
Mix together flour, spices, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture and pour in well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel right away and cool slightly (5 to 10 minutes).

Sprinkle with powdered sugar, then roll towel and cake together and cool for 20 to 30 minutes. Unroll and spread filling over cake and reroll without the towel. Set on serving plate and wrap with aluminum foil and chill 30 minutes.

title: vegetable cups
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
Spread one side of each bread slice with butter.
Gently push a bread slice, buttered side down, into each of eight 6 ounce custard cups.

title: "sweet and sour chicken wings"
directions: Fry wings in deep fat, after dipping in cornstarch and egg, about 5 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(Wing tips may be removed before cooking.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients, then add 1 quart of milk.
Mix well.
Last add beaten egg whites (3 whites).
Pour into 2 large or 3 small unbaked crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until sets in the middle.

title: country fried steak with buttermilk gravy
directions: Cut the steak into serving size pieces.
If cut is not very thin, pound lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dredge with flour, shaking off the excess.

title: garlic bubble loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, sugar, shortening, salt and 2 c. flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Combine melted butter, parsley and garlic powder.
Punch dough down; divide into fourths.
Divide each portion into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball.
Dip into the butter mixture and place in two greased 9-in x 5-in x 3-in loaf pans.
Pour any remaining butter mixture over dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans; serve warm.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Beat together, butter and sugar until smooth.
Add potatoes, molasses and buttermilk.
Mix together and add flour, cocoa and spices.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured layer pans or sheet pan.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix in blender.
Add salad oil and mix well.
Very good dressing for fruit salad.

title: tofu mushroom lasagna
directions: Squeeze tofu through two thicknesses of cheesecloth until most of the water has been removed.
Put tofu in food processor or blender and blend until smooth.
Put tofu and Parmesan cheese in a bowl and mix well.
Set aside.
Saute sliced mushrooms in oil on high heat until dry.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter cookie bars
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter for 30 seconds. Add sugars; beat until fluffy.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir Miracle Whip, juice, peel and dill weed until well blended.
Place fish on grill or rack of broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of sauce.
Grill 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce. Cook 5 to 8 minutes until flakey with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dog sauce 2
directions: Fry onion and beef together in a skillet until done; drain fat.
Mix the rest of ingredients.
Cook half an hour over low heat.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla.
Combine with dry ingredients and squash.
Bake in greased loaf pan 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hawaiian chicken(microwave)
directions: Arrange chicken in 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Rearrange chicken.
Cover and cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: waverly crackers s'mores
directions: Separate crackers and lay out on foil covered cookie sheet. Sprinkle the nuts over the top.
Bring to a boil the margarine, sugar and vanilla; boil for 1 minute.
Drizzle over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yummy!

title: fried pork chops
directions: Wash chops well and pat dry. Make egg batter with milk. Sprinkle chops with lemon pepper. Dip chops into egg batter, then roll into flour and place into deep skillet in heated oil. Turn chop when it is brown.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: In a blender mix all ingredients until anchovies are finely chopped.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve over romaine lettuce. Toss, topped with croutons and Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom with rice.
Arrange chicken over rice; dot with butter. Sprinkle onion mix over all.
Pour boiling water into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix the steak, seasonings and cream; form in patties.
Coat with crumbs.
Pan-broil in heavy oiled skillet, turning often. Remove to heated platter.
Add water; season with salt and pepper. Bring to boil; scrape.
Add butter; pour over steaks.
Serves 2.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted oleo.
Put cheese, cornflakes crumbs and dressing mix in plastic bags and shake and coat chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in well-greased baking dish or pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick chicken a la 99
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender, stir in chicken soup, flour, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups of cut up chicken and milk.
You can also add 2 tablespoons of cut up pimento.
Cook and stir until steaming.
Serve over toast or biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Note:
Mix sugar and flour together (keeps the flour from balling up).

title: green slime
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
This is to play with, not to eat!
Store in a Ziploc baggie.
Surprisingly unmessy!!

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, gradually adding sugar. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon half of the batter into a buttered and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine chocolate chips, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle batter with 1 1/2 cups.
Top with remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining chip mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves about 15.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook beef and pork until starts to brown.
Then add all ingredients, except green onions, parsley and rice.
When meat is real brown, add water to about 10-inches from top of pot.
Boil about 1 hour, then add green onions and parsley.
Cook another 10 minutes.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make 4 to 6 rolls (10 to 12-inches long and 2 to 3-inches in diameter).
Wrap in heavy foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours before cooking.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with pastry cutter.
Beat egg
yolk and water mixture, then mix into crust mixture. Take half of the dough mixture and roll out to fit jelly roll pan. Sprinkle cornflakes over dough.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add lemonade, pineapple juice and extract; mix well.
Freeze in gallon plastic jars.
Allow space at top for freezing.
Defrost 3 hours before serving.
Pour into punch bowl and chop.
Add 2 quarts 7-Up; mix well.
Serves 40.

title: easy to make salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain canned berries or use fresh ones.
Add 1 cup water to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into oblong or square pan; chill.
Combine cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Top with nuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans (if frozen) until tender.
Put drained beans in a baking dish.
Combine the soup and milk.
Pour over beans, stir. Add onion rings and mix.
Top with additional onion rings, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mt. st. helen dip
directions: Mix the sour cream and taco seasoning to taste.
Place in a mound on a large plate and flatten a little.
Layer the following on top:
1/2 cup onions and tomatoes.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese and sprinkle a few diced black olives over top.
Serve with Doritos.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from green beans.
Mix with mushroom soup and milk.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove casserole from oven. Add crushed Funyons on top.
Put under broiler until Funyons are light brown.

title: whole wheat casserole stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add salt, sage, thyme and pepper.
Stir and pour over bread.
Mix lightly.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure flour.
Add shortening and cut or rub into flour.
Add milk a little at a time.
Whip up dough with a heavy spoon.
Roll 3/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: lucy clodfelter's soda biscuits
directions: Sift together the soda, flour and salt.
Work lard into the mixture until it looks like coarse meal.
Add buttermilk gradually to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until dough feels smooth and velvety.
Roll and cut out biscuits or make with hands.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Layer in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle extra sugar-cinnamon on layers, if desired.
Pour remaining sugar-cinnamon over last biscuit layer, if desired.
Melt brown sugar and butter.
Add nuts.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Immediately invert onto serving plate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in a baking pan.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix with flour and spices.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
Spread topping over apples and pack down. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil; remove from heat.
Let cool a few minutes.
Add confectioners sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine bread crumbs, sauerkraut, eggs, milk, chopped onion, caraway seed, pepper and catsup or chili sauce.
Then after a good mixing, add ground beef or turkey.
Mix well.
Pat into a thick, flat loaf (10 x 8 or 9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Place pineapple and cheese in bowl and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and jello (do not stir).
Chill.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut stewing beef in small pieces. Brown with onion in a little water. Add water to cover it or half a pan.
Let simmer for 3 hours. Add vegetables and 1/2 cup soy sauce.
Mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add to meat and vegetable mixture, stirring constantly.
Let simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: pork chops with stuffing and apples
directions: Prepare the stuffing according to package directions and set aside.
Shake the pork chops in seasoned flour and brown in oil. Lay the pork chops in a flat baking pan.
Cover each chop with a large spoonful of stuffing and then place half of a cored apple on top of the stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chantilly cream
directions: In a small bowl, whip cream until stiff.
Add sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
This cream will keep up to two days in refrigerator.
Serve this delicious cream over berries or any other fresh fruit.

title: virgin island
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until frothy.
Pour into glass.
Garnish with pineapple star.
Makes 1 drink.

title: dirt cake
directions: First need to crush up Oreo cookies.
Mix up the pudding and milk.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Layer in dish cookies and pudding.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl, adding 7-Up last.
Add ice, orange and lemon slices.
Chill.
Serves 25.

title: denver scramble
directions: In a 10-inch
skillet
cook
ham,
mushrooms,
onion and green pepper in butter
or
margarine
over medium heat about 5 minutes or until vegetables
are
tender,
but not brown.
Beat together eggs, milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper;
add to skillet. Cook,
without
stirring,
until mixture begins to set on the bottom
and
around
edges.
Using
large
spoon
or spatula, lift and fold partially cooked egg mixture so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Continue
cooking
over
medium heat about 4 minutes. Remove from heat.
Season for taste.
Makes 3 servings.

title: powder horn mountain pork rub
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Great on pork, beef, chicken, hamburger (maybe even on ice cream?).
Will keep indefinitely in sealed container (I use old mayonnaise jar) in refrigerator.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Place cooked cauliflower in casserole dish.
Toss with Cheddar cheese, sour cream, butter, chives and onion salt.
Sprinkle top with more Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers, cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Mix well in saucepan.
Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Heat just to boiling point.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with celery seed. Mix well.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
(Can add shredded red cabbage and shredded carrots.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple crisp number 1
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first five ingredients and mix well.
Arrange apple mixtures in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make small balls in your hand.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or less.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Freeze steak for at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden.
Add steak slices.
Brown lightly about 2 minutes; remove meat.
Add green peppers and onions; cook 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce, sugar, bouillon, water chestnuts and cornstarch dissolved in water and green onions. Simmer about 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mike's crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serves a bunch.

title: nacho franks
directions: Cut tortilla shells into eights and fry in oil until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Set aside.
Arrange fried tortilla shells on a cookie sheet.
Cut and arrange a generous cube of cheese on each.
Add a slice of hot dog and a small slice of hot pepper. Stick under the broiler for a few minutes, Serve immediately.

title: grandma schmalstig's salad dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 15 minutes or blend a few minutes in a blender.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Spread beans in shallow serving dish.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread over beans.
Top with shredded cheese and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: elsie bell's favorite jam cake with burnt sugar icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add jam, eggs and sour milk.
Mix flour, soda and spices; add to this mixture.
Bake in greased layer pans at 350° until done.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar, Marshmallow Creme and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring. Boil on low heat 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate bars, chips and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into two 9-inch square pans.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses set until soft; then mix together until yellow. Add onion, peppers, mayonnaise and ham.
Refrigerate overnight. Pour out and roll in nuts.

title: mock shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion with butter until golden.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Then add green beans and tomato soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix mashed potatoes, milk and egg.
Spoon mounds over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: welsh currant cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Stir in currants.
Roll dough on lightly floured board to a 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with a round cookie cutter.
Bake on an ungreased griddle over low flame or on electric griddle heated to 350°.
Turn cookie when it is golden brown, but only turn once.

title: more
directions: Cook noodles as package directs and drain.
Brown ground beef. Drain off fat.
Add onion, chili mix, extra chili powder and tomato sauce to meat.
Let simmer until onion is done.
Add the drained corn to meat mixture.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Add mixture to drained noodles; mix and place in a casserole dish.
Place sliced cheese on top.
Place in oven and let cheese melt.

title: easy rice casserole(good for covered dish dinners)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and then margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bar
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and milk; mix well.
Press 1/2 of dough evenly in bottom of greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts evenly over dough; drizzle evenly with ice cream topping.
Crumble remaining dough mixture over ice cream topping.

title: tangy yogurt cream
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all the ingredients and beat until stiff.
Transfer the cream to a serving bowl and refrigerate, covered, for at least 30 minutes before serving.
A dollop of this light, glossy cream is a fine accompaniment for any crumb cake.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Top with Town House cracker crumbs, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi tea cakes
directions: Combine ingredients to create a biscuit-like batter.
Roll batter with rolling pin until batter is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut oval shapes any size you wish and bake at 325° until done (12 minutes). Makes one batch.

title: oriental salad(add ingredients, but delicious!)
directions: Combine chicken, peas and celery; chill. Add lemon juice, garlic salt and soy sauce to salad dressing and mix until thoroughly blended. Add salad dressing mixture to chilled chicken mixture. Add noodles and grapes tossing to blend. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown in butter, onion and celery.
Add broccoli and stir for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rice and soups.
Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in cartons.
Remove from freezer and allow mixture to reach slushy stage before serving. Yields 2 gallons.

title: tennessee corn bread salad
directions: Crumble half of cooked cornbread into bottom of large glass bowl.
In another bowl combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon.
Blend well.
Spoon half of vegetable mixture over cornbread.
Stir together mayonnaise and pickle juice in small bowl.
Spread half of dressing over vegetables.
Repeat layering.
Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: passover chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup nut crumbs, ginger, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in beaten egg, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Combine preserves, wine and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: chicken yumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a shallow dish or pie plate, mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Using a pastry brush, carefully coat each drumstick with yogurt.
Roll each one in bread crumb mixture until it is evenly coated. Arrange drumsticks on a baking sheet that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake for about 1 hour or until juices run clear when meat is pierced with a fork.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon.
Beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well between each addition. Combine flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add alternately to first mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Add shrimp and mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in a baking dish. Crush one pack of Ritz crackers with 1 stick of margarine. Place on top of casserole in dish.

title: missionettes monster cookies
directions: Mix eggs, margarine, brown and white sugar and vanilla with mixer; add flour, soda and oats.
Fold in chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Use 1/4 cup measuring cup for cookie scoop.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 40 to 50 big cookies.

title: amnor pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk, yolks and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients and add other mixture.
Fold in egg whites.

title: my mom's greens
directions: Wash turnip greens through several waters.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
In large iron skillet, put bacon grease and add greens that have been lifted out of the water.
Add salt to taste and a little sugar, if desired, and cook on medium heat until greens are almost dry.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in 1/3 cup milk.
Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Add the soaked bread; mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lumpia
directions: Cook onion, beef and sausage until brown; drain.
Cool and add shrimp and seasonings.
Spoon in wrappers.
Fold in triangles and roll.
Deep fry in oil until light brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: double mocha cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in cold coffee and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Frost with Creamy Mocha Icing.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake in 2 (10-inch) pans that have been greased and floured at 350°. Check for doneness after 35 minutes.

title: cherry salad(dessert)
directions: Drain pineapple well, juice not needed.
Soften cream cheese. Using fork, mix the crushed pineapple into the cream cheese.
Add the cherries (which have been cut into small pieces).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook, until soft, broccoli and onion.
Cook, until done, rice in water.
Mix in pan and heat, cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Drain water from broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 11 x 16-inch pan; sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame seed chicken wings
directions: Make a few slits in each wing.
Mix all ingredients in bowl, except chicken, and mix well.
Add chicken and coat
with batter. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
In wok, shallow fry chicken until cooked, about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread stuffing for fish
directions: Combine ingredients lightly.
Stuff 3 or 4 pound fish.

title: meat loaf for two
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into a loaf in baking dish. Spread more catsup in a thin layer over the top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour or until meat is done.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Add potato soup, cheese soup and milk to cooked broccoli. Cook slowly until ready to eat.

title: salsa
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Cover; chill overnight. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: chili cashews
directions: Pour olive oil into heavy frying pan.
Crush chili pequins and add to oil along with garlic powder; mix well with oil.
Add nuts and toast over medium heat for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix seasonings and nuts together thoroughly.
When nuts are toasted, sprinkle with chili powder; stir so chili powder is well mixed with nuts.
Pour into serving bowl.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onions for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and carrots.
Melt oleo and stir in stuffing mix.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 of stuffing mix; spread.
Pour zucchini mixture on and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
This may be frozen baked or unbaked.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and chop.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring to a boil 3 cups sugar and 1 quart water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add 1 large can pineapple juice, 1 can frozen lemonade and 1 can frozen orange juice.
Add 8 very ripe bananas that have been mixed in osterizer.
Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, then vanilla and flour. Mix well. Sprinkle sugar on cut cookies and bake at 325° until lightly brown.

title: ginger beef stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from beef. Partially freeze beef; thinly slice across the grain into bite size strips. Set aside.

title: bakeless pudding(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add crushed pineapple.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and chopped pecans.
Layer with vanilla wafers in serving dish.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir until thick and add fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour in graham cracker crust.
It is a very rich pie.
Does better if made the day before eating. Yields 2 pies.

title: pear salad
directions: Open and drain pears (save juice). Bring 1 cup pear juice to boil. Remove from fire and add jello.
Stir until completely dissolved (about 2 minutes). Set aside to cool somewhat and after 5 minutes, put in refrigerator.

title: pecan snowball cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat first 4 ingredients until creamy. Add flour, oats, nuts and salt.
Mix well. Shape rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool completely. Re-roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: whoopie pie cake
directions: In a small saucepan, beat 1 egg; add 1/2 cup milk and 2/3 cup sugar. Cook and stir over low heat for several minutes or until mixture begins to barely coat spoon. Add chocolate and stir until melted and mixture is thickened slightly. Cool to room temperature. In a bowl, cream butter until fluffy; add sugar and cream until light. Add vanilla and remaining eggs. Mix well. Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with remaining milk. Stir in mixture. Spread half of batter into large round circles on a buttered and floured cookie sheet; repeat with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched with a finger. Cool and remove to rack for complete cooling. Place 1 layer on serving plate and spread with filling; top with other layer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, then eggs.
Stir in pumpkin and dry ingredients.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Bake about an hour and check.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and banana cream together.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add 1 cup of cold water and stir; gradually add Cool Whip and stir until well mixed.

title: applesauce raisin biscuits
directions: *Mix 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon with 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Squeeze
excess
juice
from	strawberries.
Mix
all ingredients together and pour in two layer cake pans which are well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to full boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare rice.
Serve meat mixture over rice and top with garnishes:
chopped tomatoes, sour cream, shredded cheese, black olives and tortilla chips.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: carrot and apple cake
directions: *For lo-fat variety replace the oil with 1 cup applesauce.

title: trash candy
directions: You will need 1 small trash bag.

title: pink punch
directions: Add raspberry ginger ale to white grape juice.
Chill before serving.

title: glazed carrots(4 servings)
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and then dry.
Mix sugar with ginger. Roll carrots in mixture.
Melt butter or oleo in a skillet, then add carrots, turning slowly and often over low heat, until carrots are glazed and lightly browned.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Add vinegar, ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and sugar. Dip chicken pieces in sauce. Place in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over chicken and cover. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: diet spiced tea
directions: Bring water to a boil and pour over the other ingredients in a 5-cup teapot.
Cover and steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir and strain when serving.
Yield:
8 (1/2 cup) servings; 2 calories per serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients well, except strawberries and pie shell; cook over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Add the strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: pecan confections
directions: Beat egg
white
until
stiff but not dry. Combine brown sugar, salt
and flour and fold into egg white gradually.
Stir in nuts
and
drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: chili
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef, onion and green pepper in saucepan.
Drain grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: pineapple scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: grandma jettie's pound cake
directions: Beat real good.
It needs to be beaten ten minutes or more. Bake at 350° until done.
Use an angel food cake pan.

title: spiced apples
directions: Pare apples, quarter and core; cut each quarter into 3 thick slices.
Place in a large bowl of water and lemon juice.
Combine sugar, cloves, cinnamon sticks and vinegar in kettle; tint bright pink with food coloring.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes. Drain apples; add enough syrup at a time to make one layer deep. Heat to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes or just until apples are tender. Pack into hot jars.
Process 15 minutes in water bath.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Set cream cheese out to become room temperature.
After cream cheese has become room temperature, cream together with margarine and sugar.
Add in eggs, one at a time.
Stir flour in creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain berries and pineapple to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to jello.
Stir in pineapple and berries.
Pour in 2-quart flat dish.
Put into refrigerator until firm.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Mix. Spread over salad after set.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: mushroom and cheese quiche
directions: Toss the shredded cheese with the flour in a bowl.
Then add the beaten eggs, milk and seasonings.
Fold in sliced mushrooms. Pour the mixture into pie crusts.
Bake pies in preheated 350° oven for approximately 1 hour until the pie is golden brown and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rice with chilies and sour cream
directions: Cook rice. Combine with salt and sour cream. Arrange 1/2 of rice mixture in bottom of greased dish. Cut cheese into domino size pieces and wrap in strips of chili peppers. Place on rice. Add remaining rice mixture; dot with butter. Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible cheese burger pie
directions: Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs about 1 minute or until almost smooth. Pour over beef.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans in 350° oven 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Add fresh milk to finish filling up churn.
Put in electric or hand churn.
Add ice and salt.
Churn until ready.

title: chicken or turkey delight
directions: Combine home style vegetables, including liquid, cooked chicken or
turkey and remaining ingredients; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts.
Divide this in half; leave half out.
Pour other half in a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Spread sour cream on congealed half.
Add rest of mixture and chill.

title: jalapeno cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water; add butter, cheese and onion. Stir until cheese and butter melts.
Fold eggs into mixture.
Pour into large well-greased casserole.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour or until mixture is set.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Drain and chop mushrooms.
Soften cream cheese.
Combine mushrooms, cream cheese and seasoned salt.
Press perforations in crescent roll dough to make 2 long pieces of dough.
Spread cream cheese mixture on dough.
Roll each piece sideways.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and slice about 3/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meat, then sausage.
Add seasonings, mushroom, and Rotel Tomatoes.
Cook until tender.
Then add parsley, and green onions.
Cook for a minutes longer.
Then add all the liquid. Once it boils, put the rice in and cook about 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together shortening and brown sugar.
Mix beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Add flour, salt, buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together, adding the walnuts.
Grease 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: leek and mushroom soup
directions: In large frying pan, melt butter and saute leeks and mushrooms until almost soft, about 5 minutes.
Add stock, and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and add the potatoes. Simmer, with lid ajar, about 30 minutes.
Cool and puree in a blender.
Add cream.
Serve hot or cold.
Garnish with chopped chives, a few mushroom slices, or chopped parsley.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix the cookies and margarine together and press into a 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Freeze
until hard.	Spread the ice cream (soften) over
the frozen crust.
Freeze again.
Now make the sauce.

title: phil's easy crock-pot chicken
directions: Place clean, cut-up fryer in the crock-pot first.
Cover with the remaining ingredients.
Cook on low all day (8 hours). Simple and delicious.
Suggested side dishes are rice and a vegetable.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Slice squash in 1/4-inch slices.
Line baking dish (casserole) with alternate rows of squash, onions, salt, pepper and about 2 teaspoons of flour for each layer.
Salt and pepper should be used to taste.
Dot each layer with butter after you place flour on top of layer.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for approximately 3/4 hour.
Check after 1/2 hour.

title: crispy cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Heat a small baking pan, then bake at 375° until brown.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Mix with beater for 1 to 2 minutes the lemon pudding and cold milk.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice concentrate until thawed.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Let partially set.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until set.
Spread with topping and chill overnight.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Flavor to suit your own taste.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and spices over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs with dry milk.
Combine with cooked vegetables and bake in glass pie pan at 375° for 16 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Measure cereal and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Measure syrup and sugar into a saucepan and bring to a full boil; immediately remove from heat.
Pour over peanut butter and cereal; mix fast and well.
(Pour directly on peanut butter to soften it for mixing.)
Press into buttered 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Melt chips in double boiler; spread as icing over mixture.
Let icing cool, then cut into bars.
Freezes well.

title: sirloin tip stir-fry
directions: Cook sirloin tips or cut-up sirloin steak until well done. Put shortening in frying pan.
Cut up peppers and onions; add salt and sirloin, stir and fry on medium heat until brown.
If desired, add sauce (optional).

title: easy cheese cake
directions: By hand, mix cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix Dream Whip (directions on box), then pour Dream Whip into sugar and cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into cracker crusts; top with cherries. Makes 2 cakes.
Refrigerate.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix the ingredients well and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving and add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Serves approximately 25.

title: biscotti toscani
directions: Place almonds in a shallow pan and bake in 325° oven until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: chilled shrimp pasta salad
directions: Combine yogurt and seasonings in a large bowl.
Mix well. Combine and mix all vegetables. Add shrimp and macaroni. Thoroughly mix. Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients well. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° until brown.

title: recipe for a perfect volunteer
directions: Put in friendship, add lots of love.
Put in many, many smiles and add a barrel of happiness and another of understanding.
Add hope, helpfulness and honesty.
Add truth and patience, and lots of kindness and also some ambition and cleanliness.
Add lots and lots of faith and top it off with volunteering each week.
You will come out with one perfect volunteer.
Try it, won't you?

title: heavenly soup
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 3-quart casserole or baking dish.
Combine all ingredients (except cheeses and cream) in dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Stir in cheeses and cream.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken scampi(low-fat)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add chicken.
Brown lightly on each side (about 10 minutes).
Remove chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onion and garlic. Stir-fry until golden brown (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, mushroom and parsley.
Return chicken to pan.
Spoon vegetables over meat.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes more, until sauce is thick and fork can be inserted with ease.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Contains 254 calories per serving.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Cook water and sugar until it spins a thread.
Meanwhile beat egg whites until stiff.
When water mixture is done, slowly add to egg whites while they are beating.
(this is after they are stiff).
Then ice a cake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Add corn and soup.
