Put fries in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan; place meat mixture over the fries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put one layer of crushed Doritos on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix meat, onion, rice and soup together.
Spread mixture over chips, then layer cheese over mixture.
Top with another layer of crushed Doritos. Bake from 30 to 45 minutes at 375° or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add broth; cook and stir until thick.
Add meat, vegetables and salt.
Heat to bubbling; pour in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Arrange in a ring, rounded side down on top of hot chicken.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Makes 5 servings.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat egg; add remaining ingredients (except blueberries), in order listed, and beat with a fork until smooth.
Fold blueberries into batter.

title: green beans and corn
directions: Add salt bacon to green beans; cook on medium-high heat until almost done, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add ingredients to green beans, sweet corn, banana pepper, salt and pepper.
Finish cooking with green beans until tender to taste.
Serves 6 to 8 approximately.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in oleo; add rice and broth or consomme.
Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid, almonds and mushrooms.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Make sure liquid covers rice and check for doneness as ovens vary.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 6-quart saucepan with a large amount of water and a teaspoon of salt until done.
(You may have to add more water.)
Mix Bisquick, milk and corn meal. When chicken is done, remove and put aside. Continue to boil broth and spoon in heaping tablespoonful balls of dough.
Dough will rise to top of broth when done. Water may need to be added again before all dough is spooned in.
When all dumplings are done, serve with chicken and broth.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy and easy twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven at 375° for 1 hour, along with cleaned garlic bulb wrapped in foil.
Take potatoes and garlic out and let stand for 15 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
Slice potatoes in half and scoop out pulp into medium sized bowl.
With a fork, hand mash potatoes, adding garlic until well mashed and mixed together.
Add chicken broth, sour cream and butter to potato mixture and continue to mash with fork until desired texture is reached.
Place potato mixture back into potato shell.
Top with cheese and bake for 10 minutes or until cheese is nicely melted. May be made ahead of time and reheated or frozen for future use.

title: hot ham and cheese pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll each to form 7 x 5-inch rectangle.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice on each rectangle.
Fold dough in half over filling; press edges to seal.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: 4 layer choco pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; let cool.

title: caramel chex and pretzel mix
directions: Mix altogether in large roaster the dry ingredients.
Bring to boil the rest, except vanilla, and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Pour over cereal mix and stir to coat.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out on waxed paper and spread to cool.
Break apart and store in Ziploc storage bags.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat the 2 eggs and then add all the ingredients together. Mix even the pineapple juice from can.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.

title: chocolate chip diabetic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift salt, baking soda and flour together.
Cream margarine and add sweetener, vanilla and egg, blending well.
Add flour mixture.
Beat well; stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by level spoonfuls onto a baking sheet which has been lightly greased.
Bake for about 9 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer croutons, bacon and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: low-fat chiffon pie
directions: Cook Jell-O and pudding mix with water until thick.
Cool in pan until room temperature.
Do not allow to set hard.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve with lemon or lime slices on top.

title: honey-mustard swordfish
directions: Rinse steaks with cold water and pat dry.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Pour over steaks, cover and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add rest of ingredients.
Pour in casserole and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: quick and easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles following instructions on the back of the package.
When noodles are almost finished, add tuna and several slices of Velveeta cheese to taste.
Stir frequently until cheese is melted.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and pickles.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirty pretzels
directions: Lay pretzels on cookie sheet.
Mix together all ingredients except pretzels.
Pour mixture over pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Turn pretzels over and bake 5 more minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with small amounts of orange juice.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Boil salted water and add macaroni to boiling water. Boil until tender. Rinse with cold water.
Mix in
Cheez Whiz.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Add margarine and mix well. Cover with American cheese slices. Bake at 350° until cheese browns.

title: ripe olive casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in skillet in margarine.
Cook on low so as not to brown, but get done.
Add ground meat; cook until done.
Add tomato soup, olives, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add egg noodles (cooked and drained) and mushroom soup. Add water, if too dry.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake until bubbly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies as directed.
Cool.
Prepare chocolate mousse.
(I never can find this, so I get the Jell-O brand chocolate mousse pie mix and use only the mousse mixture, not the crust.)
Break candy into small pieces.
(Freeze the candy and then break with a hammer, or use Heath Sensations.)
Break half the brownies into small pieces and place in the bottom of a large glass bowl or trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse, half the candy bars and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Feeds up to 24 or 1 church staff.

title: kistinger's lenten favorite(tuna casserole)
directions: Heat soup, milk and cheeses together.
Stir until cheeses are melted.
Mix cooked Creamettes, soup mixture, tuna, vegetables, salt, pepper and one cup Durkee onion rings.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli whiz casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook broccoli and rice. Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wilma's peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt and baking powder; add egg.
Mix thoroughly with a fork, spread over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli shrimp soup casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Mix cream of shrimp soup, cream cheese and lemon juice in greased 2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of broccoli and soup mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: best yet pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour and flavoring; beat well.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Add batter; place in cold oven at 300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: nachos(5 minute snack)
directions: Preheat broiler; place chips on cookie sheet.
Spread refried beans on each chip.
Top with cheese, olive and onion.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve with bowl of thick 'n chunky salsa. Yields 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter; then add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Add syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Mix all and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: penuche fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt (optional). Add to the creamed mixture. Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Cool. Cut into fingers. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: tutti-frutti cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, soda and salt. Stir in candied fruit and mix well.
Form dough into rolls and chill for 1 hour.
Slice and bake for approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk into glass bowl. Add eggs, bananas, flour, soda, and nuts. Spoon into greased bread pan. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and Ranch Style beans.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Doritos.
Pour mixture over Doritos and top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green tomato crisps
directions: Soak the tomato slices in 2 gallons water.
Drain and soak 4 hours in clear water.
Change every hour. Drain and make syrup.

title: aunt estelle's sugarless cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions except use milk in the place of water.
Bake cake, remove from oven, punch holes in cake (the more the better).
In sauce pan mix fructose natural sweetener, pineapple and juice and nutra sweet.
Bring to a boil for 1-2 minutes.
Pour over cake while it is hot.
Press sugar free coconut (found in freezer dept.), sprinkle with nuts.
Can also add banana slices on top.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Blanch green peas.
Remove from heat while color is still bright green.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.
Mix peas with mustard, mayonnaise, olives, pimentos and capers.
Fill tomatoes that have been scooped out.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut butter chexs
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, peanut butter and margarine over medium heat.
Pour Rice Chex into large bowl, then pour melted peanut butter mixture over Chex.
Stir with wooden spoon very carefully until well coated.
Pour confectioners sugar into large bag.
Then pour the coated peanut butter Chex and shake well. Enjoy!

title: baked crabmeat and shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in a Pyrex dish. Sprinkle on bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and shred coarsely.
Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter or margarine in saucepan.
Over medium heat, stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Place in greased casserole and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, in a large saucepan over high heat, heat all ingredients but cornstarch to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 10 minutes, until potatoes are soft.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Have all ingredients prepared, except macaroni.
Cook and drain macaroni, then add macaroni to rest of ingredients.
Mix. Refrigerate until serving.
Make day before to allow flavors to blend.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Blend and press into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas and cube apples.
Add oranges and pineapple. Stir in sour cream, pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate.
Very refreshing!

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook pasta 11 minutes or until done; rinse and drain.
Comes in letters, numbers, pearls, all shapes.
Mix juice, milk, sugar and pudding for 2 minutes.
Fold pasta into pudding.
Add crushed pineapple, mandarin orange segments, Cool Whip, marshmallows and coconut.
Pour into a glass serving bowl.
Top with orange segments or sliced kiwi for color.
Yummy.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until
tender,
about
1/2 hour. Drain, peel and slice potatoes into
bowl.
In
skillet, fry bacon until crisp.	Remove and add onion to drippings, cook until transparent.
Add flour, stir until smooth.
Add vinegar, seasonings and water.
Bring to boil.
(This is a roux.) Add to potatoes, mix well.
May be
kept warm in a Dutch oven or heavy pot until served.
Cooking time is 3/4 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat dusted with flour in margarine.
Add mushrooms, garlic and onions.
Stir now and then until meat is tender.
Add beef broth, cover and cook 1 hour.
Then add sour cream and cook for 5 minutes.
Good served over noodles.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomato and onion as for a tossed salad.
Brown meat, drain and add taco seasoning as directed on package.
Let cool.
Add meat and kidney's to salad.
Melt cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes together in microwave or in top of double boiler.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In
large
mixing bowl, add ingredients in order given. Beat until
smooth.
Pour
mixture
into
2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar and pretzels.
Spread in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Let cool.
It will be hard, so break it up into small pieces.

title: the best pickle you ever ate
directions: Wash cucumbers and remove ends.
Slice each about 1/8-inch thick.
Fill wide-mouth gallon jar with cucumber slices to within 3 inches of top.
Place spices in center and sprinkle salt and alum evenly over slices.
Continue to fill jar to within 1 inch of top with cucumber slices.
Pack firmly into container.
Cover cucumbers with vinegar and let stand for 6 weeks.

title: professional peanut brittle
directions: Have everything ready before starting to cook.
Combine syrup and sugar in a large, heavy skillet.
Just before the mixture begins to boil, add nuts.
Stir well with a wooden spoon until it is amber colored, about 30 minutes.
Then add butter.
After a few stirs, add soda and stir rapidly.
Spread quickly in a 10 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Bake in
2 (9-inch) pans as directed on package.

title: lena's quick whole wheat bread
directions: Combine water and butter in a saucepan; heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool to 125° to 130°.
Combine 3 cups bread flour and remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir well.
Gradually add liquid mixture, beating well at high speed with an electric mixer.
Beat an additional 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover bowl; let rest for 10 minutes.

title: fruit thing
directions: Rinse fruit and drain.
Whip cream until almost peaking. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Do not overwhip.
Begin with layer of dessert shells.
Spoon on layer of fruit.
Cover with whipped cream.
Repeat until all ingredients are used or large bowl is full (usually 2 to 3 layers).
Chill and serve.

title: pork chops and potato bake
directions: Brown chops lightly in oil. Season. Combine milk, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all together and shape into balls.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together, drain.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake with rum sauce
directions: In bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.

title: bread pudding(dessert)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and crumbs.
Stir in beaten egg.
Add nutmeg.
Bake in baking pan for 30 minutes.

title: beth's cheesy chicken
directions: Day 1: Wash and place the chicken in a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Add season salt and onion slices. Cover with foil and place in fridge overnight.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grind all together starting with eggs.
Mix with dressing.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a 9-inch pie plate.
Add onions next. Spread the Hormel chili on next.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate and butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small micro-safe bowl, place butterscotch chips and 1/2 cup sweetened condensed milk and set aside.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put toasted bread in last.
Let set until bread is soaked.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning twice.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Brown hamburg and drain fat off.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly except cheese.
Cook on top of stove on medium to low heat for about 1/2 hour.
Pour over noodles and sprinkle with cheese.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and reserve 4 cups stock.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Return chicken to reserved stock.
Add soups and bring to boil.
Add tortilla strips.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add oleo when done.

title: cranberry "republican" punch
directions: Drain juice from pineapple chunks.
Reserve this juice for the punch.
Mix cranberry juice, soda and pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Chill with ice ring.
Garnish with the pineapple chunks and strawberries.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package, using the two cups of milk.
Mix with the Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of graham cracker squares.
Place 1/2 of pudding mixture on crackers.
Top with a second layer of crackers and then the remaining pudding mixture.
Top with a third layer of graham crackers.
Frost with fudge frosting.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken in baking bag(low-fat)
directions: Cover chicken real well with seasoned tenderizer.
Let set at least 20 minutes or overnight.
Now, put chicken with 2 tablespoons of flour in the bag.
Shake to coat chicken.
Put 12 ounces of water in bag and rest of the ingredients.
Put bag in a 9 x 13-inch pan and put about a 1 1/2-inch slit in the bag. Bake until done, around 40 minutes, in 300° oven.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onion, squash and zucchini in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain vegetables.
Combine soup and sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in drained vegetables.
In separated container, combine butter and stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top and then put remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or corn bread or over rice.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: squash dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add salt, pepper.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: lemonade pie\(makes 2 pies)
directions: Combine lemonade, juice and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour in graham cracker crusts.

title: quick spinach lasagna
directions: Saute the onions in cooking oil until tender.
Combine Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese, eggs, spinach, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper, sauteed onion and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese in bowl and set aside.
If using meat, cook and drain.
Cook the noodles to almost done.
Don't cook all the way.
Cook them until they're rubbery to avoid them falling apart.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 48 one-inch balls; place in lightly greased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans, shaping each into a shell.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes (dough will rise during baking).
Remove from oven and immediately press a miniature peanut butter cup evenly into each hot crust.
Cool before removing from pan.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well in large mixing bowl. Whip egg white and fold into mixture. Mix fruit and nuts with 2 cups flour. Add to mixture. Cook 2 1/2 hours at 250° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat juice from fruit cocktail
hot enough to dissolve jello. Cool.
Add cocktail and pineapple.
Cool until it starts to set. Whip 1 package Dream Whip.
Add tablespoon of sugar.
Cream Philadelphia cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Add to Dream Whip. Fold into cocktail and jello mixture.
Add nuts, if desired. Chill.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, mayonnaise and Velveeta.
Cover top with Hormel real bacon bits.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 heaping tablespoons of mix to cup.
Fill cup with hot water.
Stir and enjoy.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Place cubed angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pour over cake.
Mix well and spread out in dish evenly.
Let set in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip over and cover.
Place in refrigerator.
Best made a day ahead.

title: shrimp creole(yield: 4 servings)
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, combine celery, green pepper, onion, oil and garlic.
Heat 4 to 5 minutes on High until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, 3 minutes on High.

title: orange truffles
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in a medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from the heat.
Stir in the orange liquor and frosting. Blend well.
Refrigerate for 1 or 2 hours or until firm.

title: granola
directions: Mix together and bake in a thin layer at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, mix in raisins to taste.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, ham, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: marshmallow truffles
directions: Place marshmallows on tray and freeze for 15 minutes. Microwave chips in a bowl for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes until smooth, stirring every minute.
Dip marshmallows into melted chocolate until coated.
Roll in nuts, sprinkles, etc.
Place on wax paper lined tray.
Refrigerate or keep in cool place.

title: cinnamon apple tea
directions: Use quart size pot.
Let the tea come to a boil for 30 minutes, then add the water.
This tea will make about 1 gallon.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients.

title: bite-size cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll each biscuit out.
Spread with soft margarine and sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Roll up tight and slice. Separate on large cookie sheet and bake.
While still hot, drizzle with confectioners sugar mixed with canned milk.
Two cans make enough for a crowd.

title: pineapple loaf(no eggs)
directions: Stir the teaspoon of vinegar into the milk and let stand several minutes.
Combine the dry ingredients and gradually stir into milk with the melted butter.
Combine pineapple and molasses and stir into batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tangy butterscotch lemon pie(in honor of leo c. mcnamara, sr.)
directions: In small bowl, combine boiling water, gelatin and salt; stir until gelatin is dissolved; set aside.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook sugar, oleo, milk, beaten eggs, raisins, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon until it comes to a boil; set aside to cool. Dissolve soda in water and add to the boiled ingredients. Add flour small amounts at a time, beating well after each addition. Add nuts and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°. Turn oven to 300° and bake for 45 minutes. (Use greased and floured tube pan.)

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, corn flakes, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and onion.
Form mixture into small round meatballs.
Arrange in 10 x 15-inch baking dish. In saucepan put cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and cranberry sauce is melted.
Pour this over meatballs and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: With a mixer, beat eggs and sugar until frothy.
Add oil and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Then alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk with egg mixture.
Stir in poppy seed and chopped nuts by hand.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 2 small loaves.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add
flour,
sugar
and
brown sugar.
Beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then add alternately the flour, spices, baking powder and soda, sifted together, with the water and pumpkin.
Mix well after each addition.
When well mixed, fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until done, when tested.
Makes 4 loaves (8 x 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch).

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Cook ground chuck in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well, pat meat dry with paper towels. Wipe skillet with a paper towel.
Return ground chuck to skillet, layer potatoes, carrots, onion, green pepper and tomatoes over top, sprinkle with pepper and basil.
Cover with ovenproof lid and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate skor bar cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in two or three round cake pans. Prepare pudding as directed and refrigerate until needed.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain grease and transfer beef to a stockpot.
Add cabbage, beans, bell pepper and onions. Pour in tomato juice; add water to a little more than cover ingredients.
Stir together well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Add salt and pepper to taste and simmer until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally and adding more water as needed.

title: russian slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and pepper.
Add sugar.
In pan mix oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pour over slaw.
Seal and refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10, depending on size of cabbage.

title: sarah's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, set aside.
Cook broccoli 4 minutes in microwave. Saute onion in butter, add soup and milk; stir until blended.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir together rice, soup mixture, broccoli, and cheese in casserole dish.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown steak on one side in shortening or oil, turn and add potatoes and onions on top. Add soup, water, and onion soup mix. Simmer for about 1 - 1
1/2 hours and serve with biscuits, salad or green vegetables.

title: pecan carrot bundt cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Beat in lemon and orange peels. Combine dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture alternately with juices. Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: scalloped potatoes(60 servings)
directions: Note:
Coffee and tea consumption is down from when this book was published.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix pumpkin, ginger, milk, cloves, sugar, cinnamon, eggs, and nutmeg.
Pour into a 9-inch x 13-inch pan coated with Pam. Sprinkle cake mix dry over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Spoon cooled, melted butter over nuts.
Bake 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add rest of ingredients.
Freeze as usual.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, spinach, egg product and Italian dressing; set aside. Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer 1/3 each of noodles, spinach filling and remaining sauce; repeat twice. Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese; cover. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Uncover; bake 25 minutes more. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon cups
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salad oil and salt.
Add lemon peel and juice. Stir milk into egg yolks, add lemon mixture.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into 8-5 oz. custard cups.
Set cups in shallow pan.
Pour hot water around them 1 inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or chilled.

title: russian tea
directions: Put tea bags into boiling water.
Steep for 10 minutes. Combine sugar and water.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Stir in Sweet 'N Low.
Add fruit juices and spices.
Mix all together.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Heat before serving.

title: butter-baked pears with fruit and nut stuffing
directions: In a small bowl, combine apricots and pecans.
Using a fork, mash in 1 tablespoon butter until combined.
Set aside.
Cut pears in half lengthwise; using a melon baler or small spoon to remove cores, leaving a 1 1/2-inch diameter hole.
Cut a thin slice from the bottom of each pear so it does not tip.
In a 9-inch square microwavable baking pan, place pears with narrow ends toward the center.
Fill each pear with apricot mixture; set aside.

In a glass measure, place maple syrup and remaining 3 tablespoons butter; microwave on High (100% power) until pears are tender, about 6 minutes, basting pears with sauce halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm with low-fat vanilla yogurt or frozen vanilla yogurt, if desired.
Yields 4 portions.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry or boil ground beef and season.
Drain.
Chop lettuce, onions and tomato.
In large bowl, place chips in bottom, add meat, salad and cheese.
Top with sauce.
Stir and serve.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with shortening.
Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Batter will foam up.
Pour into pan and quickly top with some melted butter.
Bake in 375° oven for 60 minutes. Serve while warm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin side up in a microwave-safe baking dish.
Arrange thicker pieces towards edges of dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and ginger.
Top with celery.
Cover dish with waxed paper.
Microwave at High power for about 16 minutes, turning dish once if the oven is not a rotating one.
Rearrange chicken pieces.
Mix pineapple juice with brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch in a microwave-safe measuring cup.
Microwave at High power for 3 minutes until mixture thickens, stirring once.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Add pineapple chunks and red pepper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High power for another 6 to 8 minutes until chicken is tender and juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook the sugar, evaporated milk and marshmallows on high heat for approximately 6 minutes or until marshmallows have melted. This mixture will cook up to the top of your pot, so you must stir constantly.
Once the mixture comes to a full boil, reduce heat to medium.
Add 1 large package of semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1 stick of butter.
Keep this over medium heat until chocolate and butter have melted.
Remove from heat and mix with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Add chopped pecans.
Spread on cake layer(s) immediately.
Hardens quickly (like fudge).

title: shrimp and chicken jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon and crumbs.
Saute onion, celery, green peppers, parsley and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer until transparent.
Add broth, shrimp and chicken (chopped); bring to boil.
Add rice; reduce heat.
Cover and cook until rice is done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain, don't rinse.
Put in bowl.
Add butter (sliced) and most of cheese.
Mix until melted and blended well.

title: shrimp and pineapple salad
directions: Combine shrimp, pineapple, salt and paprika; mix well.
Chill when ready.
To serve, mix with French dressing; arrange on lettuce or romaine.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream well the white and brown sugars and shortening.
Add the eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add potato chips and nuts. Beat well with a spoon.
Place by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crisp sugar cookies or black walnut cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco and sugar, then add eggs. Mix until well blended.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
(You may have to work in more flour to handle good, but not too much.)
Let sit 1 or 2 hours in cool place or overnight in refrigerator.
Then make in small balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Put in greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart and press down with a fork.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine ingredients and toss with sour cream. Chill and serve.

title: ceviche de camaron: shrimp ceviche "cocktail"
directions: 1. Cooking and Marinating the Shrimp: Bring 1 quart salted water to a boil and add 2 tablespoons lime juice. Scoop in the shrimp; cover and let water return to boil. Immediately remove from heat; set the lid askew and pour off all liquid. Replace the cover and let shrimp steam off the heat for 10 minutes. Spread out the shrimp in a large glass or stainless steel bowl to cool completely. Peel and devein the shrimp if you wish: One by one lay the shrimp on work surface, make a shallow incision down the back and scrape out the (usually) dark intestinal tract. Toss the shrimp with the remaining 1/2 lime juice, cover and refrigerate for about an hour.

title: midwest garden chowder
directions: In Dutch oven or soup kettle saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add vegetables, water, bouillon, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and milk until smooth; stir into soup.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted, add parsley just before serving.
Yield 6-8 servings (2 quarts).

title: good quick pickles
directions: Drain pickles and rinse.
Wash in cold water and drain.
Cut in quarters; put back in jar.
Cook sugar, vinegar, water and spice.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and cool.
Pour over pickles; cap and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool slightly.

title: raisin sugar cookies
directions: Mix the raisins and water.
Cook until water is gone.
Cool. Cream together the sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Roll into balls from teaspoon.
Roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini into 3/8-inch slices.
Chop onions.
Cook zucchini with onion in boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.

title: frito pie
directions: Layer in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Beginning with Fritos, cheese, then onions, about 1/2 of warmed rice, then chili.
Repeat again.
When finished, cover dish with Fritos, cheese and onion mixed together.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: awesome coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per instructions. Add 1 1/2 cups flaked coconut, then bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool 10 minutes. Poke holes throughout cake. Shake can well and pour Coco Lopez (entire can) over all of cake. Cool completely. Spread Cool Whip over top of cake and top with coconut.

title: banana delight
directions: Layer each item starting with grahams on the bottom, bananas and pudding mix.
Continue layering ending with pudding on top. Crumble 6 whole grahams and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with chocolate whipped cream on top.

title: a different lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic powder, and onion and drain.
Add tomato paste, whole tomatoes, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, and oregano and cook on low heat for about 20 minutes.
Layer in a 9 x 13 inch pan in the following sequence:
Thin layer of sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, 1 c. sauce, mozzarella cheese, 3 lasagna noodles, 1 c. sauce, cheese slices, 3 lasagna noodles, remainder of the sauce, and parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for about one hour.
Then cook uncovered for an additional 15 minutes or until cheese is nice and bubbly.

title: frozen cream dessert
directions: Press 1/2 of
crumbs
in an 8-inch square pan.
Cook maple syrup and egg
yolks
over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cool.
Beat egg whites; gradually add sugar.
Fold meringue into cooled mixture.
Whip
cream
and
fold into meringue mixture.
Turn into prepared pan.
Sprinkle
with remaining
crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown meat and add onion and green pepper. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in large, greased casserole dish.
Warm together soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine; add broth and stuffing mix.
Spoon over soup mixture.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine sugar and butter and beat in eggs and pulp.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes and let cool on waxed paper.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unfold crescent rolls and press into greased baking dish (sealing perforations).
Bake in 375° oven until lightly browned. Set aside to cool while preparing vegetables.

title: pumpkin bread(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Mix thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May be frozen.

title: angel balls
directions: Crush wafers in Ziploc bag or grind in food processor.
Mix all ingredients together, roll into balls and roll in grated coconut.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Ice with favorite frosting.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread dip in dish followed by beef. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over. Spread onions, olives and tomatoes and top with cheese.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush Oreos with fingers.
Reserve 1/2 cup to garnish top of pie.
Combine rest of Oreos with margarine.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar replacements.
Add egg, water and vanilla, beating until fluffy.
Beat in carrots. Combine flour, salt and baking powder in sifter.
Sift dry ingredients into carrot mixture and blend.

title: cake for diabetics
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well with an electric mixer. Pour into a Bundt pan or an 8 x 11-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In 9-inch baking dish, mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain often, pressing meat loaf to get rid of excess fat.
After removing from oven, spread top with ketchup.
If there are any leftovers, refrigerate to make sandwiches.

title: quick-mix spritz
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
With pastry blender, cut the shortening into the dry ingredients until the mixture is full of fine lumps.
It will resemble pie crust, although not as coarse.
Measure the egg in a measuring cup.
A large egg will measure 1/4 cup.
If it does not, add water to the 1/4 cup line.
Add the egg and vanilla and beat the mixture very well.
Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Remove at once to cooling racks.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook first; boil for 2 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Mix. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool and store in cookie tin.

title: carrot chowder
directions: Brown meat; pour off drippings of fat.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper over low heat until tender.
Add tomato juice, cream of celery soup, 1 1/2 cups water, sugar, carrots, garlic and pepper.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Leave carrots a little crunchy. Pour over a slice of Swiss cheese for extra, extra goodness.

title: pecan-cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts).
Chill long enough to handle.
Shape and roll into ball or log.
Roll in chopped nuts. May be stored in refrigerator after being wrapped in Saran Wrap. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot. Simmer 30 minutes.
Cool. Blend small portions at a time.
To serve, reheat and serve with croutons.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients and beat lightly.
Mix together and bake at 425° in lined muffin tins.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Whisk eggs; add mayonnaise and soup and blend.
Stir in broccoli, onion and cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumb mixture.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy sour cream coffee cake
directions: Family and guests always rave!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend the day before.

title: nut cracker sweet muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a muffin tin.
In a small saucepan, combine apple juice, 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon. Heat to boiling. Stir in crushed crackers.
Reduce heat to medium and continue cooking until mixture is the consistency of apple sauce. Remove from heat and stir in raisins.
Set aside to cool slightly.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Blend margarine and cake mix.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Pat the rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the pumpkin, eggs, sugar, milk, salt and spices.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over cake mix in pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries and drain.
Place berries in baked pie shell. Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and salt.
Cook slowly until glossy.
Pour hot mixture over berries.
Place in refrigerator and chill before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salsa verde
directions: Mix together and serve with chips. The longer it sits, the hotter it gets!

title: chicken breasts dijon
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper in medium size bowl.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Saute chicken in large skillet in 2 tablespoons butter and the oil, turning once until golden, about 10 minutes.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.

title: peas and knepp
directions: Combine
flour, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening and blend in milk.
Place peas in large pot and add enough water to cover peas.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Drop knepp dough by teaspoon onto
top of the boiling peas.
Cook on low for 10 minutes, uncovered.	Then
cover
with
lid	and
cook 10 more minutes; drop a pat of butter on top.

title: punch
directions: Mix in large container.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: flounder amandine
directions: Cut fillets into serving portions.
Combine flour, salt and paprika; mix well.
Roll fish in mixture.
Place fish in a single layer, skin side down, in a well-greased baking pan.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons of melted butter over fish.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Saute almonds in remaining 2 tablespoons of butter until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and parsley; mix and pour over fish.
Serve at once.

title: pear pudding
directions: Mix everything together in bowl.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 servings.
Nice for breakfast or brunch.

title: blaine's best french toast
directions: Dip bread in mixture and brown on both sides in hot buttered skillet.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add the marshmallows; stir until melted.
Blend in dry jello.
Pour over popcorn.
Form into balls with buttered hands.

title: orange chiffon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well (add in order ingredients are listed).
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Mix together all ingredients except fish.
Cut cod into 2 inch squares and put in greased casserole.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and mix until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Makes 3 layers. Bake at 375° until done, 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in canister (electric freezer or hand turn) and freeze,
using salt and crushed ice alternately.
Should become firm in 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter and granola logs
directions: Stir together peanut butter and honey in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in raisins, then the granola, until blended.
Form 1 heaping tablespoon of mixture into a log, 2 x 3/4-inch.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour, until firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Season green beans to taste.
Layer beans and all other ingredients.
Top with cheese, onions and almonds.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until almonds are lightly browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A drained can of oysters may be added.

title: chinese fee-foo
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add pepper, celery and water chestnuts. Add consomme with water; bring to boil.
Add uncooked rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Stir often to keep rice from sticking.
Add water as needed until rice is done.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut up chicken; clean well.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Saute the onions.
Add chicken and sauce.
Cover and let simmer until chicken is done.
This is a good recipe.

title: ginger creams(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; add unbeaten egg.
Add molasses.
Mix flour and spices together.
Add soda to hot water and cocoa.
Add the flour and spices alternately with water, soda and cocoa mixture.
Chill several hours.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: sugar glazed peanuts
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture crystallizes and coats the peanuts (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and spread onto 2 large greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Stir and bake for 15 minutes more.
Cool and break apart.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: monterey beans and cheese
directions: Fry, drain and break the bacon into pieces.
Set aside.
Saute the onions and green pepper in bacon fat until tender.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until all the ingredients are blended and the cheese is smooth, about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter "blossoms"
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll in small dough balls. Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
After taking out of oven, chocolate kisses may be placed in middle of each cookie.

title: snappy cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Mix cheese, cayenne and salt.
Fold in cereal.
Pinch small pieces and flatten with floured glass or roll and chill to cut.
Bake on sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad i
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into paper-lined muffin tins.
Freeze.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chex after school mix
directions: In a 1-quart microwavable bowl, combine chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal (in large bowl), stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Place cereal and sugar in a large resealable bag.
Shake until cooled.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: lucy's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add milk.
Cook 10 minutes in double boiler.
Add egg yolks.
Cook until thick. Add butter and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat few minutes longer.

title: baked chicken and pepper
directions: Place single layer of chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
In 10-inch skillet, saute pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Stir in salsa, chili powder and cumin. Spoon over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese melts.
Top with cilantro.
Serve with salsa.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix potatoes, onion, soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Place in buttered 2-quart baking dish.

title: xtra-special celebration cake
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Grease 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch); dust with flour.
Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar and vanilla. Stir oil mixture and water into flour mixture real hard until well blended, about 1 minute.
Immediately pour batter into pans, dividing evenly.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; let cake cool completely. Fill and frost cake.

title: green tomatoes with pork
directions: Season chops, onion and tomatoes.
Brown chops; pour off grease.
Place in casserole; alternate layers of chops, tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with curry powder.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and soda in small bowl.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: mouth watering mexican meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl combine beef, tomato paste, sage and crackers or oatmeal.
Finely chop your onions and add to the mixture. Select the type of pepper you would like to use, making sure you test for hotness.
Add to the mixture.
Firmly press into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
About 5 minutes before being done top with the cheese and let melt on top.
Serve with a little salsa.

title: deviled nuts
directions: Spread pecans in an ungreased roasting pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine butter and remaining 5 ingredients; pour over pecans, stirring well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain on paper towels; cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
4 1/2 cups.

title: mom and dad's favorite pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
(Very important!)
Set aside. Cream the sugar, margarine and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Add flavorings.
Mix in milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: curry of lamb
directions: Brown lamb in butter with onions.
Add curry, garlic, apple and tomatoes.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Simmer, covered, until lamb is tender (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Remove lamb.
Strain sauce and thicken with flour, mixed to a smooth paste with a little cold water.
Return meat to sauce.
Serve with plain boiled rice or rice pilaf.
Serves 4.
Use chutney as an accompaniment.

title: swiss puffs
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, onion and parsley.
Spread on the rye slices.
Top each with 1/4 slice Swiss cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: seven layer spinach salad
directions: First Layer:
Wash, dry and tear 1 package fresh spinach.
Put in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Accent.

title: souffl(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt the butter and pour into two 8 or 9-inch square pans, coating the bottom thoroughly.

title: tempura
directions: Beat into a batter.
Ingredients to be dipped into batter and deep fat fried:
onion rings, eggplant slices, shrimp, green peppers, grated carrots and onions.
(Mix into batter last and drop by spoonfuls.)

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed. Mix all ingredients well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Note:
All ingredients should be at room temperature for good results (1 hour).

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Arrange asparagus in buttered dish.
Melt butter and blend in flour and salt; add milk gradually stirring constantly; cook until smooth and thick; add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour over asparagus.
Top with bread crumbs and a dot of butter.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: chicken salad(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mushrooms, water chestnuts, pecans and crumbled bacon in a large bowl.
Blend mayonnaise with remaining ingredients.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss lightly to mix; chill thoroughly.

title: cranberry-walnut relish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put cranberries in a shallow pan, 1 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with walnuts; bake 10 minutes longer, re-covered.
Remove from oven.
Stir in the marmalade and lemon juice until well mixed.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Place ingredients in bowl; mix well in mixer.
Spoon into greased casserole.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
When ready to bake, heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Bake in tube pan in 375° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together but 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour into hot iron skillet, then add rest of cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 400°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and cocoa.
Add flour and salt alternately with milk to which vanilla has been added.
Beat to smooth mixture.
Add nuts and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken; chop fine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.
This will keep several days.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until dry.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute celery and onion.
Combine all precooked ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fruit tart
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on round pizza pan; press together to form 1 solid base.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup, cocoa and salt together and cook over medium heat.
Add butter.
Remove from fire, cool and add vanilla; beat until it holds your shape.
Add chopped nuts and pour in pan to set.

title: halloween makeup
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients.
Washes off with soap and water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Combine flour, salt,
soda and nutmeg.
Stir half the dry ingredients into
the creamed mixture, then the zucchini.
Add the remaining
dry ingredients,
then
nuts
and
vanilla.
Spoon
into greased 9 x 5
x
3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix 2 eggs and oil; add cake mix and mix thoroughly.
Roll into marble size balls.
Place about 2 to 3 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for approximately 6 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool.
Spread icing on a cake and cover with another.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Blend honey and oil until blended.
Add remaining ingredients. You may add more mustard if you prefer for taste.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well. Mix in dry ingredients, stirring until blended. Stir in coconut.
Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: mama adams' fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes after it boils.
Remove from heat.
Mix in margarine. Pour in a buttered baking dish and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to the creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill batter.
Drop by tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in a 325° oven.
Store baked cookies
overnight in airtight container to soften.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry-lemonade slush
directions: For one serving:
Mix in blender 1/2 cup fresh or frozen strawberries, 1/3 cup Make Ahead Lemonade Base and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Blend until smooth.
With blender running, add about 1 cup of ice cubes, 1 at a time, through an opening in the lid until strawberry mixture becomes slushy.
Pour into a tall glass. Garnish with a fresh strawberry half, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast ahead
directions: Saute sausage and onion; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam cooking spray.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture on top; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Danish rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May uncover the last few minutes.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Put chicken in large pot with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer until meat is cooked.
Remove chicken from broth.
Chop meat into small pieces.
Skim fat from broth.
Add remaining ingredients to broth.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cook until thickened by tortillas (they will partially dissolve).
Add chicken meat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
In another bowl, mix wet ingredients.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix together.
Grease 8-inch cake pan; bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
(Mix will be sticky.)

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease a shallow casserole.
Mix soups, rice and water and set aside.
Place chicken in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: tomato cheeserole dinner
directions: Saute chopped pepper and onion in shortening.
Blend in flour; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix with other ingredients.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and sugar. Add to the bean mixture.
Chill and serve.
Better after 12 to 24 hours.

title: banana cake bake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Mix together and spread out in oblong 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: failure proof custard
directions: Combine.
Place in custard cups in water.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°, or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 individual cups.

title: corned beef hash casserole
directions: Season hen as any other fowl with salt, garlic salt, onion salt and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Then start to baste with a mixture of Vernor's and orange juice and continue to baste until bird is thoroughly cooked.
For the last half hour, spoon out orange marmalade all over the top and sides.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed until well mixed.
Blend in pumpkin, spices and salt; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour mixture into pastry-lined pan; smooth surface of filling to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan. Cool before removing rim (if spring-form pan).
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream just before serving.

title: 10 bean soup
directions: In a large pot, soak beans overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Bring beans to boil in 2 quarts water.
Reduce heat; simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes. Serves 16 people.

title: ants on a log
directions: Spread peanut butter in celery sticks.
Place raisins on top and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, oil and milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain excess juice.
Add taco mix and water (according to directions).
Mix well and cook on medium heat for a few minutes.
Add chili and mix well; add oregano, chilies and cheese.
Add hot sauce, a little at a time.
Continue cooking in slow cooker while serving.
The longer it cooks, the better the flavor.
Serve with Doritos or tostadas.

title: chocolate chug-a-lug
directions: Bring water to boil in a medium saucepan; turn heat down.
Mix sugar, cocoa and salt; add to water and blend.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour over ice cubes in tall, frosty glass.
Or chill and serve in tall glasses with a scoop of ice cream.
Serve it hot in a cup with a marshmallow and a sprinkle of cinnamon.
Makes 4 cups.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) pans.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix well between each egg.
Add flour, powder and salt alternately with milk.
Mix in vanilla and almond extract.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: asparagus-peas casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and place in baking dish.
Cover with peas and soup, mixed.
Add sliced water chestnuts and sprinkle with cheese. Melt butter in shallow dish.
Dredge the 12 pieces of bread in butter and place on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy breakfast or brunch
directions: Put bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss, cover with cheese. Combine milk, eggs and salt in blender and pour over cheese.
Top with bacon and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine.
Crumble the Ritz crackers.
Take skin from chicken, if desired.
Roll chicken pieces in butter/margarine, then roll in cracker crumbs, coating well. Place chicken in a foil lined baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Do not let this boil.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly; add marshmallows.
Put in an 8 x 9-inch pan.
Cool until set.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion together and drain.
Simmer meat and other ingredients and add noodles.
Pour all in large baking dish.
Spread on top 1 package shredded cheese.
Cook at 300° until cheese is lightly browned.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Arrange potato slices on meat.
Stir together soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and meat are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil. Layer with saltine crackers (overlap a bit). Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers; bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips over surface.
Let stand 5 minutes, then spread melted chocolate.
Refrigerate until hard. Remove foil from bottom of pan and break into pieces. Refrigerate.

title: outrageous artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In food processor, with steel blade, process artichokes until finely chopped (or chop finely by hand). Place in a large bowl with remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 4-cup souffle.

title: apricot shake
directions: Pour half of the milk into blender.
Add half of the apricot pie filling and half of the ice cream.
Cover; blend until ingredients are combined.
Pour mixture into glasses.
Repeat with remaining milk, filling and ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian tossed salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients.
Serve on chilled plates with Italian bread or crisp crackers on the side.

title: hamburger rice dish
directions: Pour 1 cup tomato sauce over rice and corn.
Add water, salt and pepper to taste.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Crumble beef over top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water.
Cover with 4 strips of bacon, cut in half.
Use a 2-quart baking dish with tight cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer until bacon is crisp.

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat beef, beans and sauce thoroughly and pour in oblong baking dish.
Crush chips.
Sprinkle on top of mixture.
Combine cheeses and sprinkle on top of chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line greased casserole with thawed tortillas.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Layer over tortillas.
Next layer beans, onions and chiles.
Mix soup and tomatoes.
Pour over top.
Top with cheese. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: carob syrup
directions: Whiz
all ingredients in blender, beginning with only a small amount of the water and adding the rest after dates are blended. Boil in saucepan for a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: madelene's brownies
directions: Melt in saucepan the butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Add together and then add to flour and nuts.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan or mini muffin tins.
Bake in oven at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown beef.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese. Put in 400° oven to keep warm.

title: winter haven salad
directions: Combine grapefruit, onions, green beans, artichoke hearts and olives in large bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper in small bowl or small jar.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over salad.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: egg noodle custard
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain. Add milk and let stand 45 minutes. Add half of the sugar, salt, lemon extract and lightly beaten yolks.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar. Fold into first mixture.
Pour into buttered mold and bake in a 325° oven for
1 hour.
Serve with Yankee Doodle Sauce.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese, corn chips and sour cream.

title: special k parfait
directions: In 2 tall glasses, layer yogurt, fruit and cereal until glass is full.
Top with extra slice of fruit and serve immediately. Yields 2 servings, 1 cup each.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, celery, milk, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Fill 1/2 cup measuring cup with meat mixture; unmold and place on baking sheet.
Combine ketchup and brown sugar; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: baked beans(crock-pot)
directions: Blend together in crock-pot and simmer.

title: ham-asparagus casserole
directions: Grease baking dish, spread ham and lay asparagus over ham.

title: cajun-style chicken stew
directions: Season and flour chicken with flour and cayenne pepper.
Brown in hot oil in a stew pot.
Remove chicken.
In the same pot, add carrots, green pepper, onion, celery and basil.
Saute 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add more oil if necessary to prevent sticking. Return chicken on top of vegetables.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, gravy, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Add water for thinner stew.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: microwave buttered potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Leave skin on potatoes.
Slice potatoes.
Put in microwave-safe dish.
Place butter over potatoes.
Cover. Microwave until done.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Fix separately melted butter and 1/2 cup Minute rice.
Saute onion; add cheese, soup, milk and eggs.
Cook until blended.
Add rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: extra-special potato salad
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cover potatoes with salted water. Bring water to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender.
Drain potatoes and cool completely.
Peel and dice potatoes.
In a large bowl, stir together potatoes and next 6 ingredients.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and all dry ingredients.
Add butter. Pour batter into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven-baked brisket
directions: Wrap brisket up tightly in foil with soup mix sprinkled on top.
Bake at 200° for 6 hours.

title: ground turkey patties
directions: Saute green peppers, onion and garlic.
Add to ground turkey the bread crumbs, Italian seasoning and water.
Mix all together. Make them into patties and fry in oil in frypan.

title: spicy garlic cheese grits
directions: Boil water and add golden quick grits and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add both cheese tubes and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6-8.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cream cheese and cream well. Blend in eggs (one at a time).
Add vanilla and almond extract. Stir in flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours in a well-greased Bundt pan.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Dry chicken pieces and combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in milk and then roll in dry mixture. Place chicken skin side up (you can remove skin if needed) in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle any left over mixture and pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake for 55 to 60 min.
It bakes a little extra crisp so cover with piece of brown paper bag first 45 min. This is especially good cold, such as for a picnic.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix together the pecans and coconut.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients together; spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: michiko's southwestern quiche
directions: Bake
pie crust per directions, perforating bottom with fork and sprinkling with chili powder.
Grate and mix cheeses and combine with eggs, chili, olives, cottage cheese and green onion. Mix
well.	Pour
mixture
onto
pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: *orange cake
directions: Squeeze orange and pour juice over 2/3 cup sugar; set aside. Grind orange peel and raisins.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add egg and mix well.
Add ground peel and raisins and mix.
Add dry ingredients, which have been mixed together alternately with the milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Use a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan. Pour orange juice and sugar mixture over top of cake immediately after removing from the oven.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Wash all fresh ingredients.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Drop batter by spoonfuls, turn once.
A good finger food for children.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise; stir until soft. Add all other ingredients and freeze.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: diet cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.	In another bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures. Crush Oreos and put 1/3 in bottom of bowl.	Cover with 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with 1/3 of Oreos.
Cover with remaining pudding mixture and top with remaining cookies.

title: vanilla, chocolate candy
directions: Toast pecans with margarine and let cool.
Melt the vanilla bark and add vanilla flavoring.
Add Hershey's milk chocolate and let melt, then add pecans and stir to coat.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in a well greased tube pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
When cool, wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: my mother's chocolate cookies(grandma honza)
directions: Mix all together in order given.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: summer salad
directions: Boil pasta and drain.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Cut slices in quarters.
Dice onions and peppers.
Combine all.
Mix soup, sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over entire bowl.
Reserve 1 cup and pour over just before serving.

title: banana blueberry bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place liners in 12 (1/2 cup) muffin cups. In a bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix in cereal and let stand 5 minutes.
On wax paper, mix dry ingredients.
Stir into batter until moistened. Stir in blueberries. Do not overmix. Spoon into cups. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: real good roast with gravy
directions: Put roast and soups in crock pot-add water enough to almost cover roast.
Cook on high for 2 hours then turn down on low and cook all day.
When done, take out of crock pot let set for a while before slicing.
Slice and put back in crock pot. use a little flour if gravy needs to be thicker.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 3 loaf pans.
Beat butter and oleo until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until creamed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour and continue beating until well mixed.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes for loaves, 2 hours for tube or until tester comes out clean.
This cake freezes very well.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in deep dish.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour batter into pan with melted margarine.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt larky's coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar, flour, nutmeg, salt and oil.
Take 1/2 cup and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Set aside topping.
To the rest, add sour cream or buttermilk, baking powder, soda and eggs.
Beat with mixer.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread(2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
lukewarm water.
Add boiling water and stir
until
shortening
melts.
Add
2 beaten eggs.
Add remaining
flour
and
yeast
mixture alternately until a soft dough is
formed.
Let
rise
to
double
in size.	Work dough down.
Divide
in
half.
Roll
each
half of the dough into a rectangle
approximately
x
17-inch or until the dough is about
1/4	to
1/2-inch
thick.
Cut
into squares.
Dip each piece into melted margarine.
Arrange in tube pan until pan is half full.	Let rise to top of pan and bake at 350° until real brown on
top.
When bread is served, let each person pull off a hunk
of
bread.
This bread can also be baked in loaf pans. Lay the
pieces
standing up in the pan so that the slices can be torn off.
This bread also freezes well.
Just tear off as much as you
need
for
a
family
meal
and wrap the rest in aluminum foil
and
freeze.	When
ready
to eat just take the package of bread from the freezer; place in hot oven and heat.

title: bread dressing for turkey or chicken
directions: Cook onion and celery in skillet with 1 tablespoon margarine until tender, then mix other ingredients.
You want this to be moist so you may need more water or chicken broth.
You can stuff your turkey or chicken or bake in pan or iron skillet at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil in blender at high speed. With motor running, gradually add oil, whip until thick.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Heat until it comes to a boil.
Apply to chicken, ribs or pork chops about the last 10 minutes of cooking, basting with the sauce to your preference.

title: no cornmeal cornbread
directions: Mix together egg, milk, sugar and oil.
Add pancake mix.
Stir just until moistened.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Cut veal in narrow strips.
Dredge meat in first five ingredients.
Put oil (olive and Wesson mixture) in an iron skillet and fry dredged meat until browned.
Remove meat from pan. Add last 8 ingredients to scrapings in pan.
Blend well.
Return meat to hot mixture and serve.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Mix rest of cake mix, oil and 1 egg. Press into bottom of 15 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together 3 eggs and sugar (cream well).
