Add milk, vanilla and 1 cup remaining cake mix.
This mixture will be runny.
Pour over crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Grate chocolate bar on top, making curls.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Beat butter, margarine, sugars, milk, egg and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture alternately until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: spicy hot chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings.
Remove tips (save for soup or chicken stock).
In a saucepan, melt butter and add hot sauce.
Simmer while preparing wings.
Heat oil to 375°.
Deep fry wings 10 minutes or until crisp.
Remove wings with slotted spoon, allowing excess oil to drain.
Immediately stir wings into butter mixture and simmer 1 minute.

title: cheddar rosemary scones
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

Use an ungreased baking sheet. 2. Combine flour, salt, sugar, baking powder, rosemary, chili pepper flakes, and cheese in a bowl stirring with a fork to mix well until the dough holds together. 3. Lightly flour a board and transfer dough to it.
Form the dough into a ball but don't over handle. Flatten dough to 3/4 inch thick disc. 4. Cut into 8 wedges. Transfer to baking sheet.
Brush with butter. 5. Bake for 15-17 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg in large mixer bowl until mixture is crumbly. Firmly press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and vanilla to a boil, boiling 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until it has melted, then put oatmeal in.
Stir until all is covered.
Then dip out on wax paper.
Let set until they get hard.

title: codfish and rice supreme
directions: Combine fish, rice, parsley, seasoned salt, onion salt and lemon pepper.
Add eggs and mix well.
Using 2 level tablespoons of mixture, firmly press into balls.
Roll in crumbs, keeping balls round.
Heat shortening to 365° and fry several balls at a time for 3 1/2 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towels. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken salad hawaiian
directions: Prepare rice mix following package directions.
Cool slightly. In a bowl mix mayonnaise, ginger, salt and pepper.
Add rice, chicken and celery.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to blend flavors.
Line salad plate with greens. Mound salad in center and surround with drained pineapple slices.

title: oyster soup
directions: Make roux with butter and flour.
Add celery, seasoning and water from oysters.
Stir 2 or 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add green onions, parsley and cream.
Bring to a boil.
Add Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and oysters.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: steakhouse cole slaw(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Mix sugar, celery seed, mayonnaise, milk and vinegar together; pour over cabbage and carrots. Mix lightly.

title: celery and carrots in parsley sauce
directions: Put celery, carrot, rosemary, bouillon and water in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, drain and keep warm.
Melt butter, stir in cornstarch, salt, pepper, onions and milk.
Cook until thick.
Stir in parsley and pour over vegetables.
Place in small casserole dish and bake for 23 to 30 minutes at 350°.
For extra crispness, sprinkle can of French fried onion on top before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add soda and mix thoroughly.
It will foam up.
In large roaster, mix nuts, popcorn and cereal.
Pour sugar mixture over popcorn mixture and toss to coat.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes. Turn onto brown bags and cool in single layer.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 20 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook to 300°.
Cook until quite thick and slightly yellow in color, (300°) stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat and add 2 tsp soda.
Stir well. Then pour into shallow buttered pan.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and form into loaf.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift 1st five ingredients together.
In a separate bowl mix egg, sour cream and milk.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Stir by hand 30 to 40 strokes.
Fold in raisins and caraway seed.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on rack and remove from pan.

title: mimosa for a crowd
directions: At serving time, place orange juice cube in each glass.
Add 2 ounces of orange juice.
Add the champagne at the last moment. Add a dash of Amaretto to each serving and add a sprig of mint.

title: rocky road pizza (cookie)
directions: In large bowl, beat butter until soft.
Add brown sugar and beat.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and beat. Spread dough in ungreased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Sprinkle peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips on hot crust.
Bake again 6 to 8 minutes until marshmallows are golden.
Cool in pan.

title: creamy caramels
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil and butter the foil; set aside.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in a 3-quart saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil slowly for 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in milk. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook until candy thermometer reads 238° (soft ball stage), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool; remove from pan. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Wrap individually in waxed paper; twist ends.
Yields 64 pieces.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Beat together Oreos, Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Beat milk, pudding and vanilla until it looks like pudding.
In large bowl or clean flowerpot, mix all together or alternate layers.
Garnish with gummy worms, if desired.

title: no. 1 sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put margarine, Coke, marshmallows and cocoa in pan on stove and bring to boil.
Put flour and sugar in mixing bowl and pour hot mixture over and beat.
Add eggs and buttermilk and beat.
Add soda and mix.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost in pan while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil whole chicken in water to cover till coming apart. Remove.
Add salt, pepper and noodles to broth and boil till tender.
Drain.
Pull chicken from bone and cut into small pieces. Mix chicken with noodles.
Add mushroom and chicken soups and sour cream.
Stir till blended.
Pour into 2 buttered casserole dishes.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can freeze one casserole.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, catsup, Tabasco sauce, onion and pickle.
Pour over shrimp.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Add remaining ingredients.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or on wax paper with rolling pin; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until smooth; mix this mixture with pudding and Cool Whip.
Put a layer of crushed cookies in bottom of a clean flowerpot (can use a bowl), then put in a layer of cream mixture and continue layering until all used, ending with cookies.
Chill.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Cook together until tender; run through juicer.
Return to vessel and cook more.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar, then put into jars. Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: wildfire
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add enchilada sauce.
In saucepan, heat the mushroom soup, water and tomatoes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 6 tortillas, a layer of soup and a layer of meat sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat layers with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: scrumptious chicken
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add in soups, sour cream, chicken and 1/3 stuffing.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining stuffing, butter and broth.
Place over top of casserole.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite eggs
directions: Mix onion, peppers, zucchini, garlic, mushrooms and potatoes in nonstick skillet.
Steam vegetables in 1/4 cup water until they begin to soften.
Beat eggs and pour over vegetables.
Stir and cook until eggs are set.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: glazed lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Continue to beat until light.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add lemon zest and juice.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool cake for 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan and spread icing at once, while cake is hot.

title: party pizza appetizers
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Add paprika, garlic powder and catsup.
Put mixture on rye bread and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Makes about 28 slices.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Place onion soup mix in chicken broth, bring to boil.
Add noodles, spaghetti and pimento.
Cook until done.
Add water as needed.
Stir in chicken.
Then add grated cheese and let melt. (Cook on top of stove.)

title: hamburger pinto beans
directions: Wash pinto
beans.
Boil
in pot adding salt and pepper to taste.
Cook
until
done, about 2 hours.
Divide hamburger in half.
Make
small meatballs of one half of hamburger.
Fry on medium-low heat until done.
Add meatballs to cooked
pinto beans. Fry
remaining
hamburger
meat.	Drain
grease.	Add remaining ingredients
to
make
a chili.
Then add mixture to cooked beans. Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Eat over rice or alone in bowl.

title: ham and crescent snack
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 4 long rectangles.
Firmly press to seal.
Place ham slice on rectangles.
Sprinkle with cheese and with mustard, starting at shortest side.
Roll up each rectangle and press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed. Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 slices.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Slice cabbage into saucepan.
Add salt and just enough water to cover.
Boil uncovered until tender.
Drain, saving water. Melt butter; blend with flour.
Add milk and 3/4 cup cabbage water.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Salt to taste.
Place layer of cabbage in casserole.
Pour part of sauce over and part of cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Sprinkle with crumbs, which have been tossed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix crackers, carrots, tomato juice, catsup, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder together.
Set aside while browning ground beef and onion.
Drain grease from the meat.
Mix the ground beef with the cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. Cool and frost with Caramel Butter Frosting.

title: scalloped potatoes and kulbasee(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, mix potatoes, boiling water, butter, cabbage and onion.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in sauce mix from scalloped potatoes package, milk and sausage.
Cover and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Cook Chinese noodles according to package directions; reserve. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or skillet.
Add garlic and onions. Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add bok choy and stir-fry for 2 minutes . Add remaining oil if needed.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to wok or skillet, along with noodles.
Stir well.
Heat until hot, about 2 minutes. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: slow cooked chili
directions: In a skillet, brown beef, drain.
Transfer to a slow cooker. Add the next nine ingredients, cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours or on high for 4 hours.
Garnish individual servings with cheese if desired.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla extract.
Stir in 3 tablespoons of milk, then gradually add enough of the remaining milk to make the frosting smooth and easy to spread.
Spread the frosting on cookies, then decorate with colored sprinkles or candies.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Add all ingredients and heat together.
Put into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: breakfast before
directions: Remove crusts from bread and break up into pieces.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
In a bowl, beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk. Pour egg mixture over bread in pan.
Spread grated cheese on top. Cover pan and set in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put raw cut (small) pieces of cabbage into greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over cabbage.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Fill with one layer of graham crackers.
Bring to a boil the butter and sugar.
Boil until foamy, not very long.
Keep stirring.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm in 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: english fish batter
directions: Sprinkle yeast over half the warm water; let dissolve.
Stir into flour and salt with oil.
Add the remaining water to make batter the consistency of thick cream.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie cottage style pancakes
directions: Use nonstick skillet with Pam.
Place eggs, cottage cheese and milk in a blender.
Whirl at high speed until creamy.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Whirl until creamy and blended.
Heat large skillet until a drop of water bounces.
Pour batter to make 3 1/2-inch pancakes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Boil carrots, celery and onions in stock until tender.
Set aside.
Add broccoli.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: syrup for caramel rolls
directions: Combine ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla.
Pour into the bottom of 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Top with frozen dough rolls or make your own.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Options:
You may add 1/2 cup chopped onion to the mixture and sprinkle bacon bits on top, if desired.

title: apple bread(2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients, sifted.
Add apples.
Mix well.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Combine 1/2 onions with chicken, celery, pimento, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Add milk to gravy and heat, then pour it over other ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Melt butter on low heat and add.
Then add milk.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad oriental
directions: Mix sour cream,
chutney,
mayonnaise and curry powder. Add remaining ingredients and toss together.
Place in refrigerator overnight.	Just
before
serving,	add 1/4 cup coconut and 1 cup chow mein noodles.	Toss lightly.
Serve immediately in lettuce cups.
Serves 8.

title: almond or pecan crunch
directions: Line a cookie sheet (with sides) with foil.
Place graham crackers on foil.
Sprinkle almonds or pecans over crackers. Bring butter or oleo and sugar to boiling point in heavy pan. Boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and nuts.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Drain apricots, reserving juice.
Cut up apricots and add to gelatin. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with miniature marshmallows and chill until firm.
Add water to reserved apricot juice to measure 1 cup.
Combine juice mixture, sugar, flour and egg.
Cook together until boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Cool.
Prepare dessert topping as directed on package. Fold cooked mixture into topping and spread on salad.
Chill. Cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute sliced hot dogs, onion and green pepper in bacon grease.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Finish filling freezer with whole milk.
Add fruit, if desired.
Freeze.

title: prairie dip
directions: Put all ingredients in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Stir just to mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When done, stir thoroughly.
Cool well.
Pour into containers to freeze as you need them.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut fingers
directions: Slice bread in 1-inch slices.
Remove crusts.
Cut slices into 4 fingers.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes until dry.
Combine peanut butter and oil in saucepan; stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Dip bread sticks in mixture; allow excess to drip off.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Let dry on rack. Makes about 44 fingers.

title: kentucky fried corn
directions: Mix cucumbers, corn and onion; fry with bacon grease.
Fry slowly so it does not brown so quickly.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Fry about 25 minutes.
Sweet green peppers can also be added if you like.

title: old-fashioned liver nips
directions: Grind liver, suet and onion with food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with a spoon to a stiff dough.
Heat remainder of beef stock (about 2 quarts; add water to make this amount, if necessary) to a hard boil.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together, adding oats and chocolate chips last.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: peasant rye
directions: Cut a round hole in top of bread.
Scoop out large enough for the dip.
Cut and save pieces of bread for dipping.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all items together, but use only 1/2 cheese.
Add more seasoning if desired.
Put in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 30 servings.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease well and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Add ingredients, without mixing, to a large bowl in the order listed.
Beat one minute with an electric mixer at moderate speed or 3 minutes by hand.
Pour into pans and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the cakes shrink slightly from sides of pans and are springy to the touch.

title: baked ginger pears(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pears, reserving juice.
Arrange pear halves close together in a baking dish, cut side up.
Set aside.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together sugar and oil (10 minutes), add salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Then add eggs (one at a time) beating between each egg.
Remove from beater, fold in carrots and flour. Pour into 3 greased/floured pans.
(The trick to this recipe is mixing the sugar and oil 10 minutes.)
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican beef burritos
directions: Sprinkle pepper and onion soup over roast.
Mix mushroom soup with water; pour over roast.
Cover tightly and cook for 2 hours at 375°, or until tender.
Remove beef and chop 2 cups.
Brown ground beef and onion in fryer.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add chopped roast beef, chilies, 3 tablespoons gravy and package of taco seasoning mix, stirring well.
Cool.
Add grated cheese, mixing lightly.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of beef mixture on each flour tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot with taco sauce.
Arrange burritos on serving tray.
Garnish with parsley and tomatoes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mom's baker's frosting
directions: Put milk into saucepan.
Heat at medium heat.
Add flour, a little at a time, with whisk.
Cook slow, over medium heat, until very thick.
Cool completely in refrigerator.
Put paste into large bowl.
Beat paste, add sugar, margarine, Crisco and vanilla. Frosts 1 (8-inch) cake or 1 sheet cake.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole(not a vegetable, but it is a side dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together pineapple and cheese; set aside. Mix together sugar and flour. Add to the fruit and cheese mixture. Spread casserole into an 8 x 11 baking dish. Sprinkle crushed crackers over top. Pour melted butter over all. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Form into a roll and refrigerate.
Slice and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar very well.
Add eggs, one at a time, salt and lemon extract.
Add alternately the flour and 7-Up.
Beat until real smooth.
Bake in preheated oven (300°) 1 hour and 15 minutes in a tube pan, not a Bundt pan.

title: french-style bean casserole
directions: Cut and measure all ingredients before starting to cook.
Fry bacon over medium heat until browned (about 8 minutes).
Remove bacon with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Brown pork chop in bacon drippings over medium heat, about 8 minutes.
Remove pork chops, stir in onion and garlic.
Saute 2 minutes or until tender. Stir in beans, tomato paste, vermouth, thyme, bay leaves, pepper, kielbasa and bacon.
Top with pork chops.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, about 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until pork is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Roll and cut out.
Bake at 500° until brown.
Makes 16 biscuits.
Each contains 65 calories and 1.5 grams fat.

title: carrot pudding cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Stir in carrots, raisins and pecans. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool completely.

title: rolled stuffed beef roast
directions: Leave carrots whole.
Cut potatoes in fourths lengthwise. Chop celery and onion fine.
Starting at one end of meat, place a layer of carrots and a layer of potatoes.
Repeat.
Put chopped celery and onion on last.
Sprinkle half the salt on top of vegetables.
Form meat roll.
Tie or pin with toothpicks. Sprinkle other half of salt on outside of meat roll.
Brown meat in a very hot oven, then add a quart of hot water.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: crunchy peanut granola
directions: Combine
first	3
ingredients	in a large mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine honey, butter and vanilla in small saucepan;
cook over
medium
heat until thoroughly heated (do not boil).	Pour over
oat
mixture; stir to coat evenly.
Spread into
two	jelly roll or sheet cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 20 to
minutes or until golden brown, stirring often.
Remove from
oven
and
cool. Stir
in
raisins and cool in airtight container.	Makes 9 cups.

title: hickory sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix well again.
Store another 24 hours.
Divide into 6 or 7 portions. Press meat together and form into rolls.
Wrap in foil and cover with water in covered kettle.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and boil 3 hours.
Remove foil, drain and cool.
Rewrap in foil; refrigerate or freeze.

title: carrots with horseradish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut carrots in julienne strips and cook in 1/2 cup boiling salted water for 5 to 7 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid. Arrange carrots in Pyrex dish.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat with chili powder and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn and sour cream.
Spoon 1 cup mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1/2 each of the chips, remaining meat mixture and cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: dill fillets
directions: Spread softened cream cheese over 1 side of fillets. Place fillets cream side up in a sprayed nonstick 9-inch square pan. Thinly slice 1 lemon and place over top of fillets. Squeeze juice of other lemon over fish. Sprinkle top of fish with dill weed. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use 1/3 of Cool Whip in pudding mix.
Save rest for topping. Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan and cover with rest of Cool Whip.

title: barbara mandrell cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Add the oranges. Mix well. Bake cake as directed on box. Let cool.

title: for the birds chickadee pie
directions: Cook ingredients over medium heat stirring constantly until thick.
Yellow cake coloring may be added as this seems to attract Orioles.

title: seasoned pork roast
directions: Place pork roast in shallow baking pan.
Mix applesauce and horseradish; pour it over the roast.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Use the meat drippings for gravy.

title: chocolate chip cookies #2
directions: First make the crust.
Use popcorn and breadcrumbs.
Put it in a pie pan.
Then make the middle.
Use cut apples and grapes and eggs.
Sugar, water, milk and popcorn kernels should be added last.
Put it in the oven for 6 minutes.
Cut it up and put whipped cream on top.

title: dressed-up wild rice
directions: Saute green onions and sliced mushrooms in butter in a medium saucepan until onions are tender.
Add rice mix and prepare according to package directions using 2 cups water and 1/3 cup sherry, omitting salt.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: moist hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw 12 hash brown patties and shred by hand in a large bowl. Add soup, milk, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper until well blended.
Spray 9 x 12 casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in the hash brown mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take out and spread cheese over top.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: concoction
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces in an oblong cake pan. Mix instant pudding according to package directions until it thickens and pour over the cake pieces.
Crumble up chocolate cookies and sprinkle over the pudding.
Pour Cool Whip on top of this.
Crumble more chocolate cookies on top of this. Refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple and dry jello together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate plunge
directions: Microwave corn syrup and cream in a large microwaveable bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture boils.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Serve as warm dip with fruit or cake cubes. Great for parties.

title: creamy cooked icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, then let cool. (Stir with whisk while cooking to get lumps out.)
Beat butter for 4 minutes. Add sugar and beat again.
Add cooled mixture and vanilla.
Beat 4 minutes again.
This icing stays soft.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix well and
place in covered container, in refrigerator. Bake as needed.
Drop
by
teaspoonful
and bake at 350° until brown.
You may
add
coconut, if desired.	This makes a huge batch and will
be	good
in
the refrigerator as long as needed.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Then add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 11 pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure 1/8 cup oil into 10-inch cast iron skillet and put in oven.
Beat eggs in medium sized bowl.
Add milk and 1/8 cup oil.
Sift dry ingredients into egg mixture and stir.
Fold in drained corn, chopped onions and jalapeno.

title: stsegte kartofler(fried potatoes)
directions: Peel and slice 6 potatoes rather thin.
Slice 2 large onions and brown in 6 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add potatoes; mix lightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, and allow to brown on the bottom.
Turn, using another pan or plate so that you can turn the whole panful as a cake.
Brown the other side, then add 2 tablespoons each of sugar and vinegar, mixed together.
Cook for 4 minutes longer, and serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it boils; add raw peanuts. Let cook until 310° on thermometer.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla, then add soda (will puff up fast).
Pour immediately on buttered cookie sheet with sides.
Clean pan and put on buttered plate.
Cool and break in pieces (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan size).

title: cold broccoli casserole
directions: Cover broccoli with boiling water for 1 minute and immediately run cold water to stop boiling process.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumbly.
In bowl, combine mayo, vinegar and sugar; mix well. Let stand until sugar dissolves.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well a few hours before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt and cold water overnight.
Drain.
Pack cucumbers into jar.
Cook remaining ingredients for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and seal jar.

title: apple cinnamon waffles
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour on center of hot waffle iron.
Serve with syrup.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/3 deep in muffin pan.
Cook at 350° until just begins to brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: maw brown's rolls
directions: Mix warm water, oil, sugar, yeast and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add flour.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Be sure to cover and let stand in warm place.
Knead.
Pull and roll individual rolls in hands.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover and let stand 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in pan for 1/2 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes at 250 degrees.
Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, do not stir.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn and mix well.

title: raisin ricotta custard pie
directions: Separate 2 of the eggs.
Put whites in small bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
In a large mixing bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, citrus peel, sugar, egg yolks and remaining whole egg.
Stir in raisins.
Stir in about 1/4 of the egg whites, then add rest of whites.

title: chinese cookies
directions: On low heat, melt butterscotch and chocolate chips. Pour over noodles and peanuts. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Refrigerate to harden. Store in airtight container.

title: pfeffernuss cookies(a german tradition)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, molasses, water, egg and anise oil in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Knead dough until stiff enough to mold.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 12 minutes or until bottoms are brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: jicama relish
directions: Peel jicamas and cut into finger-size pieces. Soak overnight in strong salt solution with a pinch of alum. Wash jicamas and drain. Peel onion and slice into strips lengthwise. Slice garlic cloves into 2 lengthwise.

Peel ginger and slice into thin strips. Cut peppers into halves. Remove seeds and slice into strips about 1/2-inch wide. Leave hot peppers whole. Arrange in clean glass jars. Prepare a solution of 3 parts vinegar to 1 part sugar with salt to taste. Boil in non-aluminum container and pour hot over jicama mixture. Seal jars tightly.

title: stuffed red peppers
directions: Mix eggs, oil and milk.
Add Romano cheese and minced garlic. Add to bread crumbs and mix all together.

Stuff each pepper half. Put into lightly oiled baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes, covered; then uncover and add tomato sauce on top of each pepper and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more, uncovered.

title: sweet and zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush on meat pieces several times during last 15 minutes of grilling time.

title: tuna potato cakes
directions: Use no salt, as the chips will add enough.

title: oatmeal chippers
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl. Blend at low speed about 1 minute. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and starting to pull away from edges of the pan.

title: lucille's caesar dressing
directions: Blend in food processor everything but the oils.
Mix well. Drizzle oils through the feed tube.
Makes 3 cups.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add soup, potatoes and sour cream.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cheese and corn flakes; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cut chicken into quarters.
Chop spring onions finely.
Mix with the salt, sugar, cornflour, soy sauce and egg.
Beat together well.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Mix with corn ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with sour cream, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix egg, lemon and cayenne. Place over low heat and add 1/2 cube frozen butter. Pierce the butter with a fork and continuously stir the egg with it. As the frozen butter melts and mixes, it prevents the egg from cooking and separating. Serve when butter is melted and mixture is creamy. Do not try to rush this process.

title: chocolate-peanut butter balls
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Chill for approximately 1 hour.
Melt chocolate bark.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Set on wax paper until chocolate cools and hardens.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Beat together 3 eggs. Mix in pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar and cinnamon. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Shake the cake mix over the top of the mixture and pat gently. Sprinkle with nuts on top of the cake mix. Melt the margarine and pour over the nuts. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°. Watch carefully near the end so that the nuts do not burn. Spoon onto dessert plates and top with whipped cream.

title: mexican buffet
directions: Mix shredded cheeses together.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, beans, picante sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Mix thoroughly by hand or electric mixer.
Spread half of the mixture on the bottom of a square baking dish.
Cover with half the shredded cheese mixture.
Add remaining bean mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Also can serve with side of guacamole and side of tomatoes.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple and sugar. Add 2 boxes of orange Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add cold water; let partially set. Fold in grated cheese, Cool Whip and nuts. Makes a large quantity.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.

title: chocolate walnut sin
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and vanilla.
Grease an 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts in pan.
Cover with mixture, then sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup cocoa evenly.
Cover with 1 2/3 cups hot tap water.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: hobo dinner(serves one)
directions: Lay 12 x 15-inch piece aluminum foil on table.
Place hamburger or ground turkey patty on it; then sliced onions, salt and pepper. Next add carrots and potatoes; salt and pepper again.
Add sliced green peppers on top.
Close up foil loosely and bake 1 hour at 375° or can cook on grill but turn often (best part is no dirty dishes).
Very good.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients (cake mix, cocoa and Dream Whip).
In a 2-cup measuring cup, add food coloring and enough milk to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add eggs and beat 4 minutes with hand mixer.
Bake at 350° in 3 layers for 20 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool.

title: king goulash
directions: Saute chopped onion and meat in 2 tablespoons of cooking oil. Cook until done, but do not brown.
Add soups and water, then mix with previously cooked noodles.
Put mixture in dish or pan it is to be served in and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
A few minutes in oven or under broiler will improve flavor.

title: spaghetti jambalaya
directions: Debone chicken by either boiling or microwaving.
Cool and pull apart.
In a large skillet, fry sausage.
Add chicken and stir-fry with sausage until brown. Add onions.
Brown with meat. Add water, garlic, hot sauce, salt and pepper (slightly over salty and peppery).
Bring to a boil. Break spaghetti into 3-inch lengths. Add raw.
Stir as necessary to prevent sticking. When spaghetti begins to soften, lower heat.
Cook until all water is gone and spaghetti is tender.
Serves 12 people.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Rind al peppers, reserve juice in a large boiler.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Let come to hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from fire and let sit 5 minutes, then add 1 bottle Certo and 5 or 6 drops of green or red food coloring.
Skim and pour in jars and seal.
Makes 10 1/2 pints.

title: cherry vanilla shake
directions: Pour diet cherry 7-Up into blender.
Add Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplement and Sweet 'N Low.
Blend well.
Add ice gradually and blend until smooth.

title: scallops louie
directions: Saute scallops and mushrooms in butter.
Combine and heat rest of ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes to heat through.

title: weeknight chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook ground beef or turkey and bell pepper for 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring frequently.
Drain excess fat.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine mix and oil, add dill, garlic and lemon pepper. Pour over crackers, stir to coat. Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: almond biscotti
directions: Combine flour and sugar; then, cut in butter until mixture resembles course crumbs.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored. Add almond extract.
Gradually beat egg mixture into flour mixture.
Fold in almonds.
Drop cookies onto a lightly greased baking sheets and flatten with a flat bottom glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Turn cookies over and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serve with coffee, tea, or hot chocolate.

title: beer butt chicken
directions: You will also need a barbecue pit.

title: play dough
directions: Mix altogether	and
heat
slowly,
stirring constantly until mix thickens
to
dough
consistency.
Take off heat and let cool. Knead 5 minutes and is ready to use.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together and carefully fold into egg mixture by hand.
Blend well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake. Allow to cool.
Cover with chocolate if using frosting.
Chill first.

title: mexican dish
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer Doritos on bottom and flatten. Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain fat.
Add milk, enchilada sauce, soups and chilies to meat mixture.
Let come to a boil; continue stirring.
Pour enough meat mixture over Doritos to cover. Then add another layer of Doritos; then add remaining meat mixture and top with remaining Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Watch to prevent scorching Doritos on top.
Grate desired amount of cheese on top.

title: microwave double decker fudge
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, put 1 cup Reese's chips and 2/3 cup milk.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir when melted and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in and pour into foil-lined 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with the flour.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
(May or may not add 1/4 teaspoon salt to dry ingredients.)

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine soup and tomatoes with green chiles in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with chips and cheese. Yield: 1 quart.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dottie's "whenever" biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
With fork or pastry blender, incorporate shortening into flour until like cornmeal.
Gradually add milk, blending with fork until spongy, mixing in all the flour.
Turn out onto floured board, kneading until smooth.
Round up on board; cover with bowl and let rest 10 minutes.
Uncover and work down.
Pat out to desired thickness and cut.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Melt butter (oleo) and set aside to cool.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with pecans.
Lay frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all. Pour melted butter over all.
Cover pan with plastic wrap or foil. Let set on countertop overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Heat the water, milk and oil to 125°.
Mix on low.
Pour liquid into flour mixture.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Beat in 1/2 cup of flour and beat 2 minutes.
Beat in about 3 cups of flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Put in pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turtle brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan melt caramels with 1/2 of the evaporated milk.
Keep warm.
In a medium bowl mix dry cake mix, melted margarine, remaining milk, and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of the dough into an ungreased 9 by 13 inch pan and bake in preheated oven for 6 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over the baked cake.
Drizzle caramel mixture over the chips.
Drop remaining dough evenly onto caramel layer.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares and enjoy.
Because of the milk, this will need to be kept in the refrigerator.

title: linguine misto
directions: Cut each
carrot
lengthwise into thin slices; then cut slices into
linguine
thin strips.
Prepare linguine as label directs; drain;
keep warm.

title: royal hawaiian hotel steak sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook for 2 minutes.

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers, pour into casserole dish. Spread crushed crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, until top is golden brown and crunchy.
Freezes well.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Add first 3 ingredients and cool.
Mix together baking soda and water.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add chocolate bits.
Bake at 350°.
For cookies bake 10 minutes.
For brownies bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: artichoke and avocado salad
directions: Toss artichoke hearts and avocados.
Combine rest of ingredients except lettuce, mixing until well blended.
Chill. Place lettuce leaf on salad plate; top with artichoke and avocado mixture.
Pour dressing over and serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk and butter.
Gradually stir in corn meal and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks. Stir into corn meal mixture.
Fold beaten egg whites into corn meal mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Set dish in a pan of water and bake in a 350° oven for 1 3/4 hours or until a knife blade, when stuck in center of bread, comes out clean.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy breakfast squares
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, milk and onion; pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix sour cream and onion soup mix. Measure out 1 cup and mix with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, nutmeg and allspice. Form into small balls and dust with flour. Brown on cookie sheet in 450° oven. Mix remaining sour cream-onion soup mixture with water. Put meatballs in chafing dish or crock-pot and cover with this mixture. Serve hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and put cleaned strawberries in the shell.
Cook the other ingredients until clear.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Pour over strawberries while still hot.

title: mrs. meadows' pralines
directions: Cook all together to
soft
ball stage.
Take off fire; add 4 tablespoons margarine and
2 cups pecans.
Bake on stove and beat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop on foil.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add milk and stir, adding water as mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and thin as desired with water.

title: kim's dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in 13 x 9 pan. Mix pudding mix and milk as directed on package. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Pour juice over cake. Put fruit on top of this, reserving some to garnish top. Spread pudding over fruit. Next, spread Cool Whip over pudding. Use remaining fruit for decoration. Refrigerate.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light colored.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oil and vanilla.
Fold in thinly sliced apples and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Place pan on rack to cool.
Cut in squares.
May be frozen.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine the spinach, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereals.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, coated with cooking spray.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares when cool. Yields 24 squares.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine.
Combine all ingredients together and stir.
Bake in greased muffin pan, filling 1/2 full.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean the fryer and sprinkle with black pepper and seasoned salt. Dot the roasting pan with butter.
Cut up the pepper, onion and carrots and place inside of the fryer. Place white potatoes around fryer.
Cover and place fryer in the pan.
Place aluminum foil over the pan to cover the fryer. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Cook celery and onion in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients until mixture is moist and sticking together.
Roll into 3 or 4-inch balls.
Deep fry balls until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, corn and bell pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: cherry brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 3 squares of chocolate and butter over low heat.
Let cool completely.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, cinnamon and chocolate mixture.
Stir until just mixed.
Pour into greased square pan. Bake for 20 minutes.
Spread cherry pie filling on top, then bake for 10 minutes longer.
Melt 1 square of chocolate and drizzle over top of brownies.

title: sugar dates
directions: Take a date and stuff half walnut inside date.
Take stuffed dates and roll in bag of powdered sugar.
Yum yum.

title: chicken and escarole with wine sauce
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and basil; dredge chicken with seasoned flour.
Reserve remaining flour.
In large skillet, heat oil and butter.
Add chicken and garlic; brown on all sides.
Turn flame to simmer.
Cover and cook chicken until tender (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Remove chicken; set aside.
Add mushrooms, wine and enough reserved flour to thicken into sauce.
Replace chicken. Top with escarole.
Cover; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes to steam escarole.
Turn out onto serving platter.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach.
Beat eggs well and add salt.
Add spinach and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes and light brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 452°.
Prepare pastry and divide into 6 portions. Roll each into 1/8-inch thick squares.
Place 1/2 cup apples in center of each.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar, dash of cinnamon and nutmeg and 1 tablespoon butter over apples.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Moisten corners of squares.
Bring 2 opposite corners of pastry over apple and press together. Fold remaining sides and press corners together.
Place dumplings in ungreased baking dish. Heat brown sugar and water to boiling.
Pour around dumplings. Spoon syrup over dumplings 2 or 3 times during baking.
Bake approximately 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no bake peanut bar cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter, salt, corn syrup, sugar and vanilla. Remove from heat.
Add cereal, nuts and coconut.
Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and boil eggplant.
Put small pieces of onions in water. Cook until tender and drain.
Put eggplant and onion in mixing bowl and mash.
Add salt, cracker crumbs, eggs, garlic powder, Romano cheese, parsley flakes, basil leaves and oregano.
Saute butter, medium onion (chopped fine), chopped celery, mushrooms, pepper, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and ground chuck.
Add to eggplant mixture.
Put entire mixture into greased casserole.
Top with grated, toasted bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt margarine in heavy Dutch oven.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat until dark golden brown.
Stir constantly.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Break up canned tomatoes and add with liquid to Dutch oven.
Add chicken broth, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in okra and simmer until okra is tender, approximately 30 minutes. Add shrimp and oysters.
Cook until shrimp curl and turn pink and the oysters curl on edges.
Remove from heat and stir in file powder to thicken.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: short ribs of beef
directions: Arrange short ribs in 3-quart casserole.
Add just enough hot broth to cover ribs.
Add onion.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on high 10 minutes.
Rearrange ribs.
Cook on medium 35 to 45 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, then buttermilk and soda together.
Mix all dry ingredients; add to egg mixture until well blended, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Check with toothpick to make sure it is done.

title: yellow sheet cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy. Add oil and beat. Add eggs and beat. Add flour, milk and vanilla. Beat.
Pour in a prepared pan. Bake in oven heated to 350° until done. Check at 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cover carrots with water and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add all the other ingredients and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Can be stored in the refrigerator for weeks.
Makes 1 quart.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chocolate wafer crumbs and butter in ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press evenly against bottom and side of pan. Bake 10 minutes. Cool.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool pasta.
Mix together all ingredients. Use your favorite Italian dressing and seasonings.
More dressing may be added as desired.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes, if wanted! Chill and serve.

title: marinated green olives
directions: Rinse olives and pat dry.
Keep jar and lid.
Return olives to jar.
Add remaining ingredients; cover tightly and shake. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in colander and rinse with hot water to defrost.
Combine remaining ingredients except corn flakes.
Pour over hash browns.
Top with crushed flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In
1 1/2 quart casserole combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and half of the onions.
Bake at 350°
for
minutes or until hot.
Then stir.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes longer.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: chili con queso
directions: Cube the Velveeta cheese and melt in a double boiler.
Add the other ingredients. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Add cup of milk, 2 egg yolks and 4 tablespoons flour; flavor with vanilla.
Put flour in bowl; add little of milk.
Mix well.
Add to sugar mixture.
Cook until thick; pour into pie shell and top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemonade, Cool Whip and juice of lemon until well blended.
Pour into pie crusts and chill at least 2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: When baked, crumble in punch bowl; add following layers:

title: laurie's stuffed shells
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef, Ricotta cheese, egg and bread crumbs.
Cook shells a little (half way) and rinse under cold water.
Put thin layer of sauce in casserole dish.
Stuff shells and place in dish.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream puffs(vannbakkels)
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add all the flour at once and stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with vanilla sweetened whipped cream or a custard.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: slow-cooked turkey and sweet potatoes
directions: Layer sweet potatoes and turkey in a 4 to 5-quart slow cooker. Mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over mixture in slow cooker.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla, pumpkin and raisins. Sift together dry ingredients and add, mixing thoroughly. Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni and hot dog bake
directions: Split wieners and cut in small pieces.
Fry in skillet until done.
Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package. Combine macaroni and cheese with wieners in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: forrest mushroom chowder
directions: In a 5-quart kettle or Dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels, crumble and set aside.

In bacon drippings, saute onion and mushrooms until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in potatoes, flour, salt and thyme until well blended. Gradually stir in broth and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Cover and simmer chowder over low heat until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in half and half; heat through and ladle into soup bowls.
Sprinkle each serving with some crumbled bacon and chervil or chives, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: ginger-garlic spicy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Brush both sides of each of 8 chicken breasts with garlic mixture.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into pieces for serving.
Place in baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain and while warm mix in dry taco seasoning (do not add liquid).
Let meat cool.
Toss with other ingredients. Just before serving, garnish with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Remove all brown from cake by scraping with a case knife.
Cut or tear into bite-size pieces.
Mix gelatin with 4 tablespoons of ice water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Mix pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Add gelatin to mixture and chill until it starts to thicken.
Check often.
Add 1 large Cool Whip to mixture.
Stir cake pieces into mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish that has a cover.
Spread evenly.
Chill until set.
Top with the medium Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Will keep several days.

title: aunt henry's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add unbeaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff.
Use teaspoon to drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: coconut no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Cook until boils. Remove from heat and let cool for 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo or butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in rice, onion flakes, salt, soup and water.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle a dash of pepper.
Bake (uncovered) in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry; crimp or flute crust.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup, eggs and salt.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Microwave:
In medium bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and steak sauce.
Mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon beef mixture around an onion; roll into a ball.
Repeat with remaining beef mixture and onions.
Arrange meatballs in 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High 3 minutes. Re-arrange meatballs; cover and cook on High for 1 to 3 minutes, until firm.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.

title: sicilian soup
directions: Remove skin from sausage and break up meat.
Brown it with onion (drain off fat).
Add tomatoes, chicken broth and basil. Bring to a boil in a large saucepan.
Stir in rosamarina (a noodle type pasta), salt and pepper.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rosamarina is done.

title: sweet roll pull-apart
directions: Place frozen rolls around in a greased Bundt pan.
Cut up margarine and drop over rolls.
Mix pudding powder, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour over rolls.
Set Bundt pan on cookie sheet.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes.
Flip Bundt pan on a plate.
Enjoy!!

title: butterhorns(dinner rolls)
directions: Mix together the yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar. Beat in the eggs with the warm water.
Let stand 15 minutes. Add the 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, salt and flour.
Knead well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Divide into 2 parts and
roll in 12-inch circle. Cut into 16 wedges. Roll up, starting with wide side.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Brush with butter. Serve warm.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot and saute leeks until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add asparagus and chicken broth.
Simmer until asparagus is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Puree in blender and reheat.
Add cream, Parmesan cheese and salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix well. Cover and refrigerate. Knead once a day for 3 days. On the fourth day, knead and divide into 5 loaves.

title: grandma's never fail sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and margarine as for a pie.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla together; add to rest of ingredients.
Form a ball and refrigerate for at least one hour before rolling.
(Dough works better when stiff.)
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thickness and use cookie cutters.
Bake for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
(Bake only until bottom edges start to turn golden.)

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening and stir in sugar, add egg and beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and stir into first mixture.
Blend in vanilla and oats (raisins).
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and powdered sugar alternately. Pour into 2 chocolate crumb crusts.
Top with shaved chocolate or sprinkles.
Freeze at least 4 or 5 hours, overnight is best. Serve frozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with dry orange Jell-O powder.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add orange juice, egg, shortening and orange peel.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Grease pan on bottom only.

title: spudnuts and glaze
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well; let rise as a sponge.

title: pizza squares
directions: Arrange 1 1/2 packages of crescent rolls in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with pepperoni.
Top with the remaining cheese and top with the rest of the crescent rolls.
Bake according to directions on the crescent rolls.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Roll in meat tenderizer, then pour heated mixture over roast. Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours, then bake, uncovered, 1 hour with barbecue sauce over top.

title: easy, healthy, no bake cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine first 4 ingredients in blender (or bowl) and blend thoroughly.
In large bowl, add instant pudding to blended mixture and mix with spoon quickly until powder is incorporated.
This step must be done by hand.
Spoon into prepared crust and smooth top.
Refrigerate several hours to firm. Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix together all ingredients and top with Ritz and melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim steak and pound well.
Cut into 6 to 8 pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat beef.
Place meat and any remaining flour mixture into rectangular baking dish or 10-inch square casserole.

title: old fashioned matzo meal sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until pale.
Add sugar.
Add juice and vanilla. Combine meal, starch, salt and grated rind.
Add to the first mixture with beater.
Beat egg whites until they hold a peak and fold in.
Bake in ungreased angel pan at 350° until the cake springs back at touch.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Mix margarine and first 4 ingredients.
Split rolls and spread with mixture.
Place ham and cheese on, then put tops back on rolls.
Melt remaining mixture and pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine Jell-O, pecans and coconut; stir in milk and vanilla. Mix well and chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Tint sliced almonds with green food coloring; put on top of strawberries as leaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine shortening and sugar in large bowl until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients; add dry ingredients to shortening and sugar mixture.
Will make 2 to 3 loaves.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch greased loaf pans for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: fastest cheesecake recipe
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Add chocolate flavored sweetened condensed milk and mix until very well combined.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
If you want to cheat, you can top this with cherry canned fruit pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated garbanzos
directions: Combine all ingredients and allow to marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Drain.
Serve with toast rounds, or as part of an antipasto tray.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Approximately 135 calories per 1/2 cup serving, 20 calories per tablespoon.

title: donna's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together.
Squeeze in lemon.
Mix in with apples.
Spread a little flour on bottom of pie plate and on top of bottom pie crust.
Pour in half of apple mixture.
Top with 1/4 stick butter.
Add remaining apple mixture.
Top with 1/4 stick butter.
Place top pie crust on; finger-crimp edges around pan.
Beat whole egg and brush over top crust.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except Triscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in small container.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, salt and soda in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk and mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
When you want some muffins, take out and fill muffin pans 2/3 for baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix will keep up to six weeks in refrigerator.

title: spring green dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan (or 2 pie pans).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (not brown).
Let cool.

title: meatballs
directions: Put hamburg and crumbs in a bowl and pour rest of ingredients over it; mix well, then shape in balls.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Stir-fry pork for 3 minutes.
Stir-fry vegetables for 2 minutes.
Return all to wok. In bowl, mix pineapple juice and rest of ingredients.
Stir into wok.
Add snow peas.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice or with chow mein noodles.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all but cheese. Pour half in a greased pan.
Spread cheese over top and then cover with rest of the mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
(I usually double this recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan and I mix the cheese up in the whole mixture.)

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan or baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: four-cheese stuffed shells with smoky marinara
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Preheat oven to 375°. Coat 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes with cooking spray; set aside. Place cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese in a food processor. Process until smooth. Combine cottage cheese mixture, Asiago and next 6 ingredients (Asiago through spinach). Spoon or pipe 1 tablespoon cheese mixture into each shell, seam sides up in 1 prepared dish. Pour 3 cups Smoky Marinara over stuffed shells. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella. Repeat procedure with remaining stuffed shells, Smoky Marinara and Mozzarella in remaining prepared dish. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Prick potatoes	all
over
with
a fork; cut in halves. Arrange cut side
down
in	a
circle
on paper towel in oven. Microwave on
High	7 to 9 minutes, rearranging potatoes once, until almost
tender.
Remove from oven; let stand directly on flat heatproof
surface 5 minutes, until tender.
Put bacon in 2-quart bowl.
Cover
with a paper towel and microwave on High 4 to 4
minutes,
until bacon is crisp, rotating bowl 1/4 turn once.
Drain
bacon
on
paper towel.
Add onion to bacon fat; cover with	waxed
paper and microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring
once,
until
onion
is	tender.
Stir
in remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Microwave uncovered 5 to 6
minutes, stirring
every
minutes,
until
thick and bubbly.
Cut potatoes
in
half again.
Add and stir to coat. Microwave on High
to
minutes, until potatoes are hot. Crumble bacon into
bowl.
Stir
to mix.	Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings; 99 calories per serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes; let cool.
Add fruit juices and bananas (these can be blended together).
Mix well.
Put in a large container, cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 1/2 to 3 hours before use.
Thaw to a mushy texture.
Add ginger ale and serve.
Serves 30 with seconds.

title: granny grubbs' tomato soup
directions: Add all ingredients together, except the milk.
Bring to a boil, then let cool enough to pour in the milk without curdling.

title: too easy to be good coffee cake
directions: Place one layer of frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Combine brown sugar, dry butterscotch pudding and pecans.
Sprinkle half of the mixture on the frozen rolls.
Add another layer of frozen rolls and the remainder of the pudding mixture.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Cover with a towel and let rise overnight. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Invert on serving plate.
Serve with bacon, eggs, coffee or milk.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: two-potato swirls
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
In separate saucepans, cook white and sweet potatoes or yams in a small amount of boiling salted water, covered, about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly; put on top of rhubarb.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then at 350° for another 20 minutes.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in a covered casserole dish at 250° for 2-4 hours.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix with drained fruit cocktail.
Add vanilla to well beaten egg.
Fold egg into first mixture and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Better when served warm with whipped cream.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut celery in 1-inch pieces.

Slice onions 1/4-inch thick; cut chicken in 1-inch bites. Cook celery, onion, seasonings, fat and meat covered over low flame for 1 hour. Add soy sauce, mushrooms and bean sprouts. Serve with rice. For Chow Mein, serve on crisp Chinese noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Cream together butter, white and brown sugar.
Add eggs and the vanilla.
To this, add flour, soda and baking powder.
Then add Rice Krispies, noodles and nuts.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: josie's meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, onion, oats, bread crumbs, tomato soup, salt, garlic and pepper all together until well blended.
Put on counter or hard surface.
Pat out flat in 1-inch thick rectangle shape.

title: chicken curry
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cook carrots and mash them.
Add cooled margarine.
Add eggs. Mix flour, baking soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Add sugar. Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: smothered steak
directions: Mix flour and seasonings together.
Coat meat that has been cut into strips.
In oil or butter, saute onion and pepper that have been cut into strips.
Add mushrooms.
Put vegetables aside and brown coated meat.
After cooking meat on both sides, reduce heat and add tomato sauce or stewed tomatoes (if desired).
Simmer until beef is thoroughly cooked and tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sauce should be fairly thick.
If it's not, you may add a small (1 to 2 tablespoons) amount of flour to thicken.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook Pet milk, sugar and margarine until soft ball forms. Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Beat and pour in buttered dish.

title: boiled and browned potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets until tender, cool.
Cook until tender bell pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Leave jackets on potatoes and chunk.
Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bell pepper, onion and bacon. Dot with 1 stick butter and bake in oven at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: instant chocolate mix drink
directions: Mix well and store in sealed container.
To serve, add 1/4 cup mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Stir and top with marshmallows if desired.
Stir or shake dry mix well each time you use it.
Great for camping!

title: salad
directions: Prior to serving use Wish-Bone Italian dressing to cover the salad.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples and remaining ingredients in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Add top crust.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: baked potato and cheese casserole
directions: Twenty-four hours ahead:
Boil potatoes after peeling and mash. Include all ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish, cover and refrigerate.
To serve:
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and parsley or sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour, uncovered.

title: buttermilk chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken with celery and seasoning salt until tender. Discard celery and remove chicken from the bones.
Reserve 2 cups broth. Set aside.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts in skillet.
Remove to ovensafe covered casserole.
Pour salsa over chicken, cover and bake at 350° until fork-tender.
Top with remaining ingredients, reserving cheese; cover and bake additional 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and return uncovered to oven and bake until cheese melts.
Serve with flour tortillas, refried beans and Mexican rice.
Serves 4.

title: cherries cooper's chex treat
directions: Mix pretzels, cereal, M&M's, peanuts and chocolate chips in a large bowl.
Melt white chocolate and pour over mixture.
Mix carefully and fill up large freezer bags.
Place in freezer.
Keep in freezer until you are ready to serve.

title: easy one dish meal
directions: Arrange in well-greased casserole in order given, adding salt after each layer.
Pour tomatoes over all and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
If liquid evaporates while cooking, add more tomatoes or soup stock to keep it moist.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add reserved flour with soda and extract.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chilies and cheese.
Pour layer of mixture.
Spread chilies and cheese.
Alternate, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until firm but not too dry.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
In a bowl, mix egg, milk and bread crumbs together.
Add crab meat and other ingredients. Mix well.
Form into little patties.
Fry in butter until brown. Serve on a hamburger bun or just as is.

title: honey-whole wheat bread
directions: Mix whole wheat flour, honey, shortening, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Add warm water.
Blend 1 minute on low speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in enough of the flour, one cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.

title: taco veggie salad
directions: May add broccoli, carrots, cucumbers, etc.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: *Beat and make meringue.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar well.
Roll into balls and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Melt chocolate and dip peanut butter balls halfway into it.
Refrigerate for another 24 hours. Tastes like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, using a wire whisk or a fork, beat the egg and egg whites until foamy.
Add the milk, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Beat well;
set aside.

title: el paso burgers
directions: Chop onion and green pepper finely.
Add onion, pepper and taco seasoning mix to meat.
Mix well.
Divide meat into eight equal pieces and form eight patties.
Grill or fry to desired doneness.
Turn hamburgers at least once during cooking.
Top with a slice of cheese, sour cream and salad.
Serve immediately on a hamburger bun.
Makes 8 burgers.

title: salsa
directions: You may use more hot peppers if you like or any kind you want.

title: hamburger cutlets parmesan
directions: Combine ground beef with parsley, salt and pepper. Shape into patties. Coat with flour. Dip into beaten eggs and then dip into bread crumbs. Brown patties in skillet containing oil. Place in baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese. Pour spaghetti sauce over meat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: potato breakfast burritos
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: italian flat bread(focaccia)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Set aside.
Add flour.
Work dough until it does not stick when poked with finger.
Place dough in an oiled bowl, turn to coat and cover with a towel.
Let rise for 4 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Punch down and let rise for 10 minutes before rolling.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Blend bananas in blender.
Mix frozen orange juice according to directions on cans.
Combine sugar, water, juices and bananas.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Coat each potato with fat or butter.
Roll potatoes in cereal mixed with salt.
Bake in greased baking pan at 350° until lightly browned and heated through, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
I have added Parmesan cheese or other seasonings to the corn flake mixture for a different taste.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix and place in icebox 24 to 48 hours and serve.
Serves 10.

title: hamburg dip
directions: Cook hamburg to a fine consistency.
Drain out fat.
Add in the next 8 ingredients and stir well.
Cut up cream cheese and add to mixture.
Cook on medium heat until cheese is all melted.
Stir well.
Then add your Parmesan cheese.
Mix and enjoy with nachos. Always serve warm.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch squares.
Brown in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Remove from pan.
Add gravy mix to pan.
Mix in 2 cups water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in rest of ingredients; add meat.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish with remaining ingredients; mix well.
