On top, crush potato chips and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: reese balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and roll into balls; put into refrigerator until chilled.
Put paraffin and chocolate chips into double boiler until melted.
Using toothpick, dip each ball into hot paraffin, being sugar to cover each ball.
Place on wax paper until cool.
Makes about 60 to 70 balls.
Place in tightly covered container.
Stores well.

title: wieners chinese style
directions: Put everything together and bring to boil.
Then add cornstarch and water (blended) gradually.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add hot dogs and serve with rice or Chinese noodles.

title: charle's pumpkin cake
directions: Mix milk, pumpkin, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan, line bottom and sides with waxed paper.
Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix and pecans over mixture.
Press chopped pecans into cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over this and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: hidden valley chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken wings in butter, pepper and vinegar.
Put in baking pan and sprinkle with one package of dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Use dressing as dip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in margarine.
Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add Jiffy corn muffin mix to egg and corn mixture. Add onions and green pepper.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread with sour cream.
Then top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
After removing from oven, cover for a few minutes before serving.

title: low-fat, low calorie fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in margarine in large skillet for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir often.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and broth.
Cook 2 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Gently toss fettuccine and cheese.
Top with vegetables.
Serve.
Yields 7 cups or servings (179 calories per serving and 5.8 grams fat).

title: chinese rice
directions: Mix all above ingredients together in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
This can be baked at any temperature the oven is on, but time may need to be adjusted. Cook until all moisture is absorbed.
Stir once or twice during baking.

title: creamy corn
directions: Thaw corn and place in casserole.
Mix in cream cheese and butter.
Heat in oven 30 minutes (350°).
Also can be heated easily in microwave.

title: cranberry-apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts, apples and cranberries.
Spoon in pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter in first bowl.
Mix sugar and Rice Krispies in second bowl.
Then mix together.
Form into balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Dry on wax paper.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender; add in curry powder.
Cook 1 minute; stir in soup, water, shrimp and thyme. Simmer a few minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken breasts for approximately 2 1/2 hours. Debone and cut into bite-size pieces. Place in buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inch). Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle poppy seeds on top and salt and pepper to taste. Melt butter and add crushed Ritz crackers; mix well. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt and syrup.
Stir well and add pecans.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: rainbow bananas
directions: Cut
bananas into 1-inch pieces, roll in Jell-O powder. Lay on mound of Cool Whip.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Spread into greased and floured 9-inch square cake pans.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; spread over previous mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until dark golden brown.
Cakes will settle in center when cool.

title: pecans
directions: Preheat the oven to 275°.
Spray a cookie sheet with a light coating of vegetable cooking spray and set aside.
Beat the egg whites with the water until frothy, but not stiff.
In a separate bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Dip pecans in the egg whites, then in the sugar and cinnamon mixture and again in the egg whites.
Spread the nuts in one layer on the cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour (turn every 10 minutes in the last half hour of baking time).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins, nuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased, floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch cake pan. Bake in moderate oven - 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Cool.
Can spread with confectioner's sugar butter icing, sprinkle with orange rind, decorate with whole walnut meats, or good plain!

title: bars made with tomato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into a greased
9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick is clean.
Frost with plain white frosting while warm. I use canned cream cheese frosting.

title: nutritional cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add honey, eggs, and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased sheets.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix
soups,
milk,
chicken,
celery,
onion
and water chestnuts
together well.
In separate bowl, mix melted margarine and
dressing.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour 1/2 of dressing mix, then pour all of chicken mixture and cover with rest of dressing mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncover baking until brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Mix and pour in 15 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°, with pan of water beneath dish, for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
May serve with ice cream.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: easy cake
directions: Melt oleo (in big pot).
Pour in cake mix.
Mix 1 egg, beaten. Mix well.
Add nuts and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased lightly. Press out.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs (beaten) and sugar with mixer. Pour on top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, not too long.
Toothpick will not come out clean.
Refrigerate, then cut in squares when cool.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Place paper liners in twelve medium (about 2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, ginger and salt in medium bowl. Make a well in center. Blend molasses, egg whites, oil and milk in small bowl. Pour into well in dry ingredients. Stir just until ingredients are moistened. Spoon into lined muffin cups, filling each about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until centers spring back when touched lightly. Makes 12 muffins.

title: butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Gradually beat in flour until just blended.
(If dough is too stiff, beat in 1 or 2 tablespoons water.)
Let dough stand in refrigerator overnight. Be sure to wrap dough in plastic wrap.

title: jello fruit salad pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and juice from cherries.
Add cherries, pineapple and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add bananas.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells. Let sit 4 or 5 hours before cutting.
May serve with Cool Whip.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in 2 3/4 cups flour, soda and salt.
Stir.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining flour and sugar and cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Mix together the sugar and butter.
Add flour, nuts, coconut and eggs.
Spread in long pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in oil, zucchini and lemon peel.
Stir liquid mixture into flour until moistened. Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, marshmallow cream and milk in a mixing bowl.
Use electric mixer to cream ingredients until smooth.
Add drained, crushed pineapple.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together, including cocoa.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: company chicken
directions: Layer chicken, soup, yogurt and dry soup mix in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meringue cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat the egg whites with the salt until they are frothy.
Add the vinegar and beat the whites until they hold soft peaks.
Beat in the granulated sugar, a little at a time, and food coloring, if desired, until it holds stiff, glossy peaks. Beat in the liqueur and chocolate chips, if desired.
Spoon level tablespoons of mixture 2 inches apart onto baking sheets lined with foil, shiny side down.
Sift the confectioners sugar lightly over meringues and bake in a preheated 300° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave the meringues in the oven with the door closed for about 4 hours or until they are firm.
Let the meringues cool on racks and store them in airtight containers. Makes about 45 cookies.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup milk; set aside.
Combine cake mix, oleo, 1/3 cup milk and 1 cup pecans.
Press 1/2 of this cookie dough into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Cook tomatoes until soft then skin.
When cool, dice.
Cook in pan (like enamel; not aluminum pan).
Dice peppers and onion; cook all together.
Cook until thickens.

title: cinnamon-sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Blend in sour cream.
Add flour, mixed with soda and baking powder to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Blend well.
Spoon half the batter into 9-inch tube or Bundt pan which has been buttered and floured. Sprinkle half of the nut mixture over batter.
Spoon in remaining batter and top with nut mixture.
Place in cold oven; set at 350°. Bake 55 minutes.

title: lentil and nut roast
directions: Mix and put in greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dot top with butter.
Cook at 350° until it thickens, usually about an hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients; mix in the cucumber and the onion.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion slaw
directions: *You can be the judge for the amounts of these.

title: bey spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and green pepper.
When done, add rice and beans.
Turn down and simmer for about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cola cake
directions: *Note:
For a firmer cake, use 16 ounce package pound cake mix stirring in 1/3 cup powdered chocolate drink with orange peel.
Use cola for liquid; bake as directed.

title: pavlova
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut 9-inch circle of greaseproof paper. Brush paper with oil and place on greased oven tray.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Turn oven on to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir ingredients until mixed, but do not beat.
Can be lumpy.
Add 1 cup of blueberries that have been gently rolled in sugar.
Put into greased muffin tin; usually fills 12 cups of tin, but if you only fill 10 or so, put a little water in empty spaces.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Have fun eating muffins.

title: hamburger squash casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; put in casserole.
Add meat on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until meat is done.

title: hot water cornbread(hush puppies)
directions: Boil water.
Then add slowly to sugar and cornmeal until mixture is to a dough; form shape into crescent forms.
(You may need to add more hot water, sometimes less but it is important to watch the consistency of dough.)
Fry in peanut oil deep enough to cover hush puppy over medium to high heat; cook until golden brown.

title: nancy's flower market mustard
directions: Blend mustard and vinegar and let stand overnight.
Next day, add eggs, salt and sugar.
Cook over double boiler 10 to 15 minutes or unti thick. Pour into small jelly jars.

title: french cheesecake
directions: Mix butter and crushed zwieback in bottom of spring-form pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla with electric mixer. Pour into spring-form pan on top of zwiebacks. Cook for 20 minutes at 350° or longer if necessary to set, then add next layer. Combine sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and pour over cooked cheesecake. Return to the oven at 475° for 15 minutes. Cool and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: scripture cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch angel food pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: orange jubilee
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients; process for 1/2 minute or until ice cubes are crushed.
Makes five 1-cup servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Cook broccoli until thawed only.
Mix soup, mayo and pepper.
Layer broccoli on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; then layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Add soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top; then buttered crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover the last 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in hot water.
Sort and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and let boil 15 minutes.
Remove from stove to sink.
Add baking soda, stir, rinse and drain.
Put in cooking pot.
Cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil. Add salt and bacon and cook until tender.
Add catsup and sugar.
Put into baking dish. Bake at 350° until center boils.

title: dried apple stack cake(old fashion style)
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and ginger. In a separate bowl, blend molasses, brown sugar, butter and eggs. Stir dry ingredients into molasses mixture to form dough.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts. Place each piece of dough in center of well-greased and floured pie pan, pressing to edges of pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Do not bake more than 20 minutes. Spread hot cake layers with Apple Filling and stack.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: You will need cup cake cups, paper or foil.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon or sausage.
Roll crescent rolls into casserole dish (glass works better).
Beat eggs and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over eggs and then sprinkle bacon or sausage over cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until edges are slightly brown, egg is cooked and cheese has melted.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, 1 tablespoon sugar and water until thick. Pour over beaten egg whites.
Mix.
Add 4 to 6 tablespoons sugar and vanilla and mix.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Makes approximately 12 biscuits.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, add pumpkin, sugar, water, oil and vanilla together.
In another bowl, mix together flour (Wondra), baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add nuts and raisins, then put mixtures together; stir well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 large loaf in greased loaf pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil 8 to 10 potatoes until soft.
Let potatoes stand until cooled.
Once cooled, peel the potatoes and dice them into a large bowl.
Add 1 can peas and carrots.
Add approximately 10 average sized dill pickles, diced.
Add approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Add mustard (enough to give it color).
Add salt and pepper for flavor.

title: fried okra patties
directions: Drain cooked okra and mash well.
Add egg and mix well.
Add salt, flour, corn meal, black pepper and baking powder; mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Yields 14 to 16 patties.

title: tater tots hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, drain off grease.
Salt to taste and add soup.
Put mixture in layers with Tater Tots in baking dish. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place apples in pan.
Mix corn syrup and hot water; pour over apples.
Mix together margarine, oats, brown sugar, flour and salt until crumbs form. Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini until smooth. Fold in dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pioneer biscuits
directions: Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Mix other ingredients and roll out on wax paper.
Cut and dip both sides in melted butter. Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender.
Saute bacon, onion and bell pepper until bacon is crisp.
Crumble bacon.
Drain excess water from squash.
Add all ingredients together and bake in a 2-quart casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more.

title: excellent sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
(May also let dough chill one hour.)
Roll into walnut size balls.
Flatten cookie with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes four dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind red and green peppers with onions, then scald with hot water and drain.
Add salt, vinegar, mustard seed and sugar to pepper mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour and bottle.
Makes 7 pints.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix with sour cream.
Let stand overnight. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: For Each Sandwich:
Spread 1 slice of bread with 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Top with second slice that is spread with 1 tablespoon jelly.
Spread top and bottom with 1 tablespoon softened margarine.
Dip in mixture of egg, beaten with milk. Grill on both sides until lightly browned.

title: butterscotch morsel candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels in double boiler; add corn flakes.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on tinfoil.
Let set for about 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix per cup of hot water.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Cream potatoes, adding butter and milk.
Add 2 ounces cheese to mixture.
Brown ground beef; add seasoning.
Pour fat off ground beef.
Add ground beef mixture to creamed potatoes.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and formed a slightly hard crust, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frosted apple brownies(yields 4 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed on an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and pecans. Pour batter into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting while slightly warm.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: quick and easy clam chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook bacon and onion until crisp; stir in undiluted soup, clams, cream and milk.
Heat slowly, stirring several times, but do not boil.
Refrigerate overnight to allow clam flavor to strengthen.
Reheat without boiling at serving time.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if glass dish).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs evenly.
Top with remaining ingredients, ending up with coconut on top.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely at room temperature.
Yields approximately 36 bars.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together well.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add small amount of milk and egg yolks; mix well. Add rest of milk and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add 4 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
butter and syrup.
Add flour, salt and eggs. Add
vanilla and pecans.
Bake in a baked shell at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and pimentos; combine in a bowl. Separately combine sugar, vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: sante fe skinny dip
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water for 3 minutes. Drain; set aside.
Position blade in food processor bowl.
Add beans.
Process until smooth.
Spread on lettuce lined serving plate.
Combine sour cream and spice mix.
Spread over bean layer. Top with chilies.
Position blade in food processor bowl; add broccoli, lime juice and garlic.
Process until smooth.
Spread broccoli mixture over chilies and top with 1 cup cheese, green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with baked tortilla chips.
Yield: 15 servings.
Per serving - Calories: 69 (23% from fat), Fat: 1.7 g (0.9 saturated), Cholesterol: 5 mg., Sodium: 287 mg., Carbohydrates:7.7 g, Fiber: 1 g and Protein: 5.6 g.

title: southwestern dip
directions: Add taco seasoning to meat after draining. Add all other ingredients.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and shape into loaf. Bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: rhubarb cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put 1/2 in bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan.
Place cut up rhubarb over this mixture.
Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add cherry pie filling and flavoring. Pour over rhubarb.
Add the rest of oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream on top.

title: honey baked apples with walnuts
directions: Peel upper half of apple only.
Coat peeled apple with honey, then roll in chopped walnuts.
Place apples in roasting pan and divide butter and raisins between cavities.
Squeeze fruit juice over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour in water and bake in oven.
When apples are cooked (approximately 40 minutes in 375° oven), remove and set aside.

title: meat dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage in slow cooker until done.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Keep warm and serve in slow cooker.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind oranges and cranberries; add 2 cups sugar and let stand about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drain pineapple; let pineapple juice come to boiling point.
Add enough water to Jell-O to make about 3 cups; mix with Jell-O.
Add to orange, sugar and cranberries along with nuts, celery and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Will keep as long as it lasts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls the size of a quarter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 32 balls.

title: six-layer bake
directions: In a greased casserole, make a layer of each ingredient in the order given.
Season each layer.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Blend whipped topping and condensed milk.
Add pie filling, blending well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate 7 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and combine with other ingredients (except chow mein noodles).
Bake, covered, in greased casserole for 30 minutes, and then uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour chow mein noodles over top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: salmon salad
directions: Combine salmon, celery and green peppers.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Serve on lettuce leaves with cracker.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini (whole) in boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Cut in halves and scoop out centers.
Mix pulp with remaining ingredients.
Fill zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Garnish with crisp bacon.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Rub potatoes with oiled paper towel.
Steam potatoes until done (not soft).
Cool.
Blend garlic, basil, parsley in blender. Add herbs to vinegar and mix salt and pepper to taste. Pour dressing over the potatoes, toss and chill.
Serves 6.
Calories: 240 per serving.
2.6 gm. fat, 9% fat.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix oatmeal, milk, egg, onion and seasonings in large bowl.
Add meat mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in large loaf pan.
Serves 8.
Also delicious cold for sandwiches!

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: date with a ritz
directions: Mix together pecans, dates and milk.
Cook over medium fire until thick, approximately 4 minutes.
Stir constantly (be careful; it will stick).
Put small amount on a Ritz cracker. Bake in oven at 350° for 6 minutes.
Drizzle glaze of powdered sugar and water, mixed, over each cracker.

title: beth's chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, beating well after each one. Measure dry ingredients together and add flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Add flavoring.
Add chocolate chips and nuts, mixing well with a wooden spoon.
Spray tube pan with Pam. Put into a cold oven and bake for 90 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage stand at room temperature until soft.
Mix cheese with sausage; add Bisquick.
Three to 5 tablespoons of water may be added if too thick.
Let mixture stand overnight.
The next day, make balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Check after the first 5 minutes.
You may need to flip them.
Yield: 80.
Freezes well.

title: gorilla bread
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar. Flatten biscuits to put a piece of cream cheese inside; close.

Roll in a ball and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Chop nuts. Put 1/2 in bottom of Bundt pan. Layer 10 biscuits and pour part of margarine and brown sugar on top. Layer again and pour rest of mixture on top. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: mocha meringue
directions: Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff,
adding
salt,
sugar, vanilla and vinegar gradually while beating.
Spread 2 squares of meringue on
two
6 x 9-inch pieces of brown paper.
Set on lowest level of
oven
and
bake at 275° for 1 hour or longer. When done, meringue will lift off paper easily.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes. Beat egg yolks and add sugar, lemon juice and salt. Cook mixture over boiling water until consistency is like custard. Add grated lemon rind and softened gelatin and stir thoroughly. Cool. Beat egg whites with remaining 1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks form. When custard mixture begins to thicken, fold in egg whites. Fill crumb crust with filling and chill. Spread with whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put sugar, mustard, red pepper, celery seed, garlic salt, salt and catsup in quart jar.
Stir well and finish filling jar with vinegar.

title: weekend chili
directions: Cook ground beef 4 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
If desired, top with chopped onion and shredded cheese.

title: imposters
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Combine crumbs, sugar, butter and peanut butter in a mixing bowl.
Mix until smooth. Press dough in pan.

title: rainbow ice cream dessert
directions: Tear cake in small pieces.
Divide in thirds, place in bowls. Sprinkle 1 pkg. dry Jello over each bowl of cake pieces and toss lightly with fork till cake is well coated.
In a 10 inch tube pan, put strawberry cake pieces in bottom, spoon strawberries over cake.
Spread 1/3 of the ice cream over strawberries.
Repeat with lime cake, blueberries, ice cream, orange cake, oranges and ice cream.
Freeze until firm (overnight).
Unmold and frost with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Later you can wrap the cake in a plastic bag to keep fresh.
Slice and serve.
Makes 16 servings.
Will keep in the freezer for a while.

title: bonnie's chicken bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture over chicken parts in baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Delicious served with rice.
Some prefer cream of celery soup.
Couldn't be easier to make!

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts together.
Press into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese together; beat. Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with milk. Let sit until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with more Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cider citrus punch
directions: In large kettle, combine cider, undiluted concentrates and brown sugar.
Stir until thawed and sugar is dissolved.
Tie cloves and allspice in cheesecloth bag.
Add to cider.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard spice bag. Serve punch hot!

title: honey peach butter
directions: In large kettle, cook the peaches in water until soft.
Press through a sieve.
Measure 12 cups pulp.
Return to kettle.
Add sugar and honey.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick (1 1/4 hours).
Pour into hot jars, leave 1/4 inch headspace.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling bath.
Makes 6 pints.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over frozen broccoli to thaw; drain.
Melt margarine in a 10-inch casserole dish.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the rice, Cheez Whiz, celery, onion, broccoli and melted margarine.
Pour into the greased casserole and bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas snow caps
directions: Beat
egg
whites
to
which
cream
of tartar has been added, until
stiff, but not dry.
Add peppermint extract and salt.
Add sugar
gradually
and
beat until well blended and smooth.
Save some
of
the
candied cherries for topping the cookies, but
add the
rest, a few at a time, to egg mixture. Cover
cookie
sheet with
plain
brown
paper.
Drop
cookie mixture by teaspoonfuls onto the paper.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes.
Let
stand
a few minutes after removing from oven, then
remove
warm cookies with a spatula and place on a rack. Top with remaining cherries. Yield:
about 30 cookies.

title: arroz con pollo burrito
directions: Combine chicken, taco spices and 3/4 cup water in large skillet.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Remove chicken mixture; set aside.
In same skillet, saute rice in hot oil until golden.
Add remaining 2 1/2 cups water, tomato sauce and lemon pepper seasoning.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken mixture, tomato and onion.
Blend well.
Heat 5 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup filling on each tortilla.
Fold in sides; roll to enclose filling. Place burritos, seam side down on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in frying pan at 400° until golden brown.

title: eleanor's great molasses cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add molasses and egg.
Add dry ingredients gradually. Chill!
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press (flatten) with glass (wipe with damp cloth first) dipped in sugar (fancy "cut glass" pattern preferred).
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together.
Pour this over the first 5 ingredients just before serving.

title: minnesota "crab" cakes
directions: Combine sea legs, bread crumbs, onion and parsley in a medium size bowl. Stir in milk, egg, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; mix well. Shape into 8 patties, adding additional bread crumbs if mixture is too moist.
Working in batches, pan-fry in butter in large skillet. Cook 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings at $.96 each.

title: cranberry claret pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients; stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add the fresh cranberries; cook slowly until all the skins pop open.
Add grated lemon peel.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Top with crisscross strips of pastry. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with sour cream and mayonnaise.

title: aunt sharon's dessert
directions: Take ice cream out of freezer so it will soften up.
While waiting for the ice cream in a food processor, crumble Oreo cookies.
In a mixing bowl, combine Oreo crumbs and melted butter. Press this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put the pan in freezer for about 15 minutes.
Take out pan.
Spread ice cream evenly over top of cookie.
Freeze for about 3 hours.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain thoroughly.
Mix together beaten eggs, milk and salt.
Break up bread.
Add grated cheese and sausage (sprinkle mustard over sausage).
Pour into greased glass baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix margarine with sugar, blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add syrup and vanilla. Pour into 13 x 10 x 2-inch pan that has been greased. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Beat egg with flour and sugar.
Add rhubarb.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and flour together.
Sprinkle over rhubarb mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Place All-Bran, crushed shredded wheat, oats and warm water in mixing bowl, stirring until smooth.
In another bowl, cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat in the combined flour, soda and salt, alternating with buttermilk.
Add cereal mixture.
Put in a gallon jar and place in the refrigerator.
Use desired amount of mixture as needed to prepare muffins.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Muffin dough keeps well in refrigerator for approximately 1 month.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain any extra fat.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and beef mixture.
Toss lightly.
Add tortilla chips and Catalina dressing.
Toss again.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with proper amount of water.
Add pineapple, cranberries, sugar and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine with cottage cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.
Add eggs, onion, pimento and salt.
Bake in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole about 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: In a large pan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly until smooth. Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill until firm, about 15 minutes. Yields 48 bars.
These are delicious!
My grandchildren request a pan of this instead of a birthday cake.

title: joanne's "breakfast for a crowd"
directions: Brown potatoes and onions in oil.
Use large saucepan to melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper until you form a paste. Gradually add milk to make a cream sauce.
Add sour cream and parsley to sauce.
Add potato/onion mixture.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Mix onion, meat, frozen vegetables, soup, milk and 1/2 cup of cheese together and pour into casserole dish.
Place the rest of cheese on top.
Place Tater Tots on top of cheese, close together.
Can add more cheese if you like.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
This freezes very well.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and other spices.
Microwave on High power for 5 minutes in a 3-quart bowl with meat and other ingredients that have been stirred well.
Microwave 14 minutes on High.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream oleo until real creamy.
Add some sugar, then peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and add rest of sugar (may take more sugar).
When pliable, form eggs or bite-size peanut butter balls.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Dip in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini until halfway cooked; season to taste.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion until soft and transparent; season to taste.
Layer on top of zucchini.
Add sliced tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Eat immediately.

title: okra with rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and reserve.
To bacon grease add onion and okra and saute.
Then add rice, seasoning and broth and bring to boil.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and salt together; set aside. With an electric mixer beat together shortening, butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip slightly into beaten egg white and roll in chopped nuts.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake for 5 minutes, remove and press thumb on top of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes more.
Cool, then fill thumbprint with jam just before serving.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add bread and rest of ingredients; mix well.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Beat together the cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla flavoring for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Place paper cupcake liners in muffin tin.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each liner.
Fill with mixture (24 liners).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
When cool, place cherry pie filling on top and place in refrigerator.
Can use any kind of pie filling.

title: oreo teen delight
directions: Take 3/4 package of cookies and mix with melted butter.
Press in bottom of 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with softened ice cream. Top with caramel and freeze overnight.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and remaining crushed Oreo cookies sprinkled on top.
Can be made and kept as long as ice cream will keep.

title: cauliflower salad-romanian(salata de conopida)
directions: Wash cauliflower, divide into florets and boil in salt water. Drain well and place in salad bowl. Pour dressing of oil, vinegar and salt on top. Serve hot or cold.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Empty yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine with sugar; cream together with egg in a large bowl.
Add yeast, water and flour. Stir until well mixed.
Put into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes or so (dough can be refrigerated for several days in an airtight container).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order.
Grease and flour 2 to 3 small bread pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If batter is put in 1 large loaf pan, bake at least 1 hour.
